{"title_page": "Michael Atkinson (Inspector General)", "text_new": "{{short description|American intelligence official}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Michael SwamprAtkinson\n|image       = Michael K. Atkinson official photo.jpg\n|office      = [[Inspector General of the Intelligence Community]]\n|president   = [[Donald Trump]]\n|term_start  = May 17, 2018<br/>On leave: April 3, 2020 \u2013 present<!-- May 3, 2020 -->\n|term_end    = <!-- May 3, 2020 -->\n|predecessor = Charles McCullough\n|successor   = Thomas Monheim (acting)\n|birth_name  = Michael Kevin Atkinson\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|5|16}}\n|birth_place = [[Oswego, New York]], U.S.\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|spouse      = Kathryn Cameron\n|education   = [[Syracuse University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]])<br/>[[Cornell University]] ([[Juris Doctor|JD]])\n}}\n'''Michael Kevin Atkinson''' (born May 16, 1964) is an American attorney. He worked for the [[United States Department of Justice]] for approximately 15 years, before becoming the second [[Inspector General of the Intelligence Community]]. He assumed office on May 17, 2018.\n\nAtkinson is known for alerting Congress in September 2019 to a whistleblower complaint about President [[Donald Trump]] pressuring Ukraine to investigate [[2020 United States presidential election|political rival for the presidency]] Democrat [[Joe Biden]] and his son [[Hunter Biden]]; [[Trump\u2013Ukraine scandal|the scandal]] eventually led to [[Impeachment of Donald Trump|Trump's impeachment]] and acquittal.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn April 3, 2020, President Trump dismissed Atkinson, saying he \"no longer\" had confidence in the Inspector General. Atkinson will be removed from his office in 30 days, as outlined in a letter sent from Trump to the Senate Intelligence Committee on April 3.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |first1=Natasha |last1=Bertrand |first2=Andrew |last2=Desiderio |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/03/trump-fires-intelligence-community-inspector-general-164287 |title=Trump fires intelligence community inspector general who defied him on Ukraine |website=[[Politico]] |language=en |access-date=2020-04-04 |date=2020-04-03}}</ref> He was put on administrative leave immediately after the letter's publication.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/04/chuck-grassley-intel-community-watchdog-firing-164831 |title=Trump Defends Firing \u2018Terrible\u2019 Intel Community Watchdog as Republicans Question Sacking |work=[[Politico]] |language=en-US |accessdate=April 5, 2020 |date=April 4, 2020}}</ref>  A bipartisan group of senators demanded a more thorough explanation from Trump regarding the ousting.<ref>https://www.cbsnews.com/news/senators-demand-more-information-from-trump-on-ousting-of-intel-community-inspector-general</ref><ref>https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/10/barr-russia-trump-durham-178690</ref><ref>https://www.deseret.com/utah/2020/4/9/21215155/donald-trump-coronavirus-mitt-romney-inspector-general-firing</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAtkinson was born in [[Oswego, New York]], and was raised in [[Pulaski, New York]].<ref name=\"SenQuestion\">{{cite web |title=Response to Questionnaire for Completion by Presidential Nominees |url=https://www.intelligence.senate.gov/sites/default/files/documents/q-matkinson-011718.pdf |publisher=United States Senate |accessdate=September 20, 2019}}</ref> He graduated from Pulaski Academy and Central School in 1982<ref>{{cite news |first=Mark |last=Weiner |url=https://www.syracuse.com/politics/2019/09/inspector-general-who-received-trump-complaint-is-pulaski-native-syracuse-grad.html |title=Inspector General who received Trump complaint is Pulaski native, Syracuse grad |newspaper=[[The Post-Standard]] |location=[[Syracuse, New York]] |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> and earned his [[Bachelor of Arts]] from [[Syracuse University]] in 1986 and his [[Juris Doctor]] from [[Cornell Law School]] in 1991.<ref name=\"SenQuestion\" />\n\n==Career==\n===Legal career in private practice and the Justice Department===\nAfter graduating from law school, Atkinson was admitted to the District of Columbia Bar,<ref name=\"DCBar\">{{cite web |title=Find members |url=https://join.dcbar.org/eweb/DynamicPage.aspx?Site=dcbar&WebCode=FindMember |publisher=[[District of Columbia Bar]] |accessdate=September 20, 2019}}</ref> and joined the law firm of [[Winston & Strawn]], where he worked for 11 years, first as an associate and then as a partner.<ref name=\"ConfirmationStatement\">{{cite web |url=https://www.intelligence.senate.gov/sites/default/files/documents/os-matkinson-011718.pdf |title=Statement of Michael K. Atkinson, Nominee for Inspector General of the Intelligence Community before the United States Senate Select Committee on Intelligence |date=January 17, 2018 |publisher=United States Senate}}</ref>\n\nAfter the [[September 11 attacks]], Atkinson decided to enter public service, and worked for the U.S. Department of Justice for 15 years. He was a trial attorney in the [[United States Department of Justice Criminal Division|Justice Department's Criminal Division]], Fraud Section, from 2002 through 2006 and [[Assistant United States Attorney|Assistant U.S. Attorney]] in the [[United States Attorney for the District of Columbia|U.S. Attorney's Office for the District of Columbia]] from 2006 through 2016.<ref name=\"ConfirmationStatement\"/> Atkinson then moved to the [[United States Department of Justice National Security Division|Justice Department's National Security Division]].<ref name=\"ConfirmationStatement\"/><ref name=\"Cohen\">{{cite news |first=Zachary |last=Cohen |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/23/politics/ic-ig-michael-atkinson-whistleblower-complaint/index.html |title=Whistleblower controversy thrusts little-known Trump appointee into the limelight |work=[[CNN]] |date=September 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMajor cases on which Atkinson worked while in the Justice Department included the prosecution of former [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] [[William J. Jefferson]] on corruption charges (of which Jefferson was convicted) and the campaign finance investigation into [[Mayor of the District of Columbia|D.C. Mayor]] [[Vincent C. Gray]] (which was closed in 2015 without charges being brought). Atkinson received the Attorney General's Award for Distinguished Service for his work on the Jefferson case.<ref>{{cite news |first=Morgan |last=Chalfant |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/463115-meet-the-trump-appointed-ig-at-center-of-whistleblower-drama |title=Meet the Trump-appointed IG at center of whistleblower drama |work=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]] |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Inspector General of the Intelligence Community===\n{{Further|Trump\u2013Ukraine scandal}}{{Trump\u2013Ukraine scandal}}\nAtkinson became [[Inspector General of the Intelligence Community]] (ICIG) in May 2018.<ref name=\"SenQuestion\" /> He was nominated to the position in November 2017 by President [[Donald Trump]]<ref>{{cite news |first=Debra J. |last=Groom |url=https://www.nny360.com/news/trump-nominates-pulaski-grad-to-intelligence-post/article_57315ce4-d954-52b0-b24d-8a2215946980.html |title=Trump nominates Pulaski grad to intelligence post |newspaper=[[Watertown Daily Times]] |date=November 12, 2017}}</ref> and was confirmed by the [[United States Senate]] by [[voice vote]] on May 14, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.congress.gov/nomination/115th-congress/1252 |title=PN1252 \u2014 Michael K. Atkinson \u2014 Office of the Director of National Intelligence, 115th Congress (2017-2018) |website=[[Congress.gov]]}}</ref> At his confirmation hearings, Atkinson indicated that he would bring order to the troubled ICIG's office, which had a reputation for dysfunction, and pledged to revive a whistleblower program that had become virtually defunct under the previous Acting Inspector General,<ref name=\"BertrandLippman\">{{cite news |first1=Natasha |last1=Bertrand |first2=Daniel |last2=Lippman |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/09/23/atkinson-trump-ukraine-whistleblower-scandal-1508594 |title=The intelligence watchdog at the center of Ukraine firestorm |work=Politico |date=September 23, 2019}}</ref> saying that he would \"encourage, operate, and enforce a program for authorized disclosures by whistleblowers within the intelligence community that validates moral courage without compromising national security and without retaliation.\"<ref name=\"ConfirmationStatement\"/> Restoring the whistleblower program was a major priority among members of the [[Senate Intelligence Committee]].<ref name=\"BertrandLippman\"/>\n\nIn August 2019, Atkinson, as inspector general, received a formal complaint from a whistleblower within the [[U.S. Intelligence Community]] who stated that they had learned, in the course of normal duties, that Trump had [[Abuse of power|abused his power]] \"to solicit [[Foreign interference in the 2020 United States elections|interference from a foreign country in the 2020 U.S. election]],\" specifically by pressuring a foreign government ([[Ukraine]]) to investigate former Vice President Joe Biden and his son Hunter Biden.<ref name=\"WapoComplaintReleased\">{{cite news |first=Devlin |last=Barrett |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/house-intelligence-committee-releases-whistleblowers-complaint-citing-trumps-call-with-ukraines-president/2019/09/26/402052ee-e056-11e9-be96-6adb81821e90_story.html |title=Whistleblower claimed Trump abused his office and that White House officials tried to cover it up |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"NYTComplaintReleased\">{{cite news |first=Eileen |last=Sullivan |authorlink=Eileen Sullivan |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/26/us/politics/whistleblower-complaint-released.html |title=Whistle-Blower's Complaint Says White House Tried to 'Lock Down' Ukraine Call Records |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref> The whistleblower, a [[Central Intelligence Agency]] (CIA) officer detailed to the White House,<ref name=\"Detailed\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/26/us/politics/who-is-whistleblower.html |title=Whistle-Blower Is a C.I.A. Officer Who Was Detailed to the White House |first1=Adam |last1=Goldman |first2=Michael S. |last2=Schmidt |first3=Julian E. |last3=Barnes |date=September 26, 2019 |newspaper=The New York Times |authorlink1=Adam Goldman |authorlink2=Michael S. Schmidt}}</ref> submitted the report to Atkinson under the provisions of the [[Intelligence Community Whistleblower Protection Act]] (ICWPA).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.justsecurity.org/66211/qa-on-whistleblower-complaint-being-withheld-from-congressional-intelligence-committees/ |title=Q&A on Whistleblower Complaint Being Withheld from Congressional Intelligence Committees |work=[[Just Security]] |date=September 17, 2019 |first=Kel |last=McClanahan}}</ref> \n\nAtkinson looked into the complaint, and interviewed several government officials whom the whistleblower identified as having information to substantiate his claims.<ref name=\"Detailed\"/> On August 26, having found the complaint to be both \"credible\" and \"of urgent concern\" (as defined by the ICWPA), Atkinson transmitted the complaint to [[Joseph Maguire]], the acting [[Director of National Intelligence]] (DNI).<ref>{{Cite web |first=Margaret |last=Taylor |date=September 17, 2019 |url=https://www.lawfareblog.com/mysterious-whistleblower-complaint-what-adam-schiff-talking-about |title=The Mysterious Whistleblower Complaint: What Is Adam Schiff Talking About? |work=[[Lawfare (blog)|Lawfare]]}}</ref> Under ICWPA, the DNI \"shall\" forward a complaint deemed credible and of urgent concern, within seven days of receipt, to the [[Senate Intelligence Committee|Senate]] and [[House Intelligence Committee]]s. The Trump administration, however, withheld the complaint from Congress; [[Steven Engel]] of the Justice Department's [[Office of Legal Counsel]] issued a determination saying that the acting DNI did not need to give the complaint to Congress because, in the opinion of the OLC, the complaint was not related to \"an intelligence activity\" under the acting DNI's authority.<ref>{{cite web |first=Jacob |last=Schulz |url=https://www.lawfareblog.com/olc-issues-opinion-about-urgent-concern-determination-whistleblower-complain-dni |title=OLC Issues an Opinion About the \"Urgent Concern\" Determination on the Whistleblower Complaint by the DNI |work=Lawfare |date=September 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first1=Matt |last1=Zapotosky |first2=Devlin |last2=Barrett |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/justice-dept-rejected-investigation-of-trump-phone-call-just-weeks-after-it-began-examining-the-matter/2019/09/25/6f7977ce-dfb5-11e9-8dc8-498eabc129a0_story.html |title=Justice Dept. rejected investigation of Trump phone call just weeks after it began examining the matter |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=September 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Engle |first1=Steven |title=\"Urgent Concern\" Determination by the Inspector General of the Intelligence Community |url=https://www.justice.gov/olc/file/1204586/download |website=justice.gov |publisher=[[United States Department of Justice]] |accessdate=September 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nClashing with Maguire,<ref name=\"Cohen\"/> Atkinson himself notified Congress about the existence of the whistleblower report.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://thehill.com/policy/national-security/462464-timeline-the-trump-whistleblower-complaint |title=Timeline: The Trump whistleblower complaint |last=Bowden |first=John |date=September 21, 2019 |work=The Hill |accessdate=September 23, 2019}}</ref> In a letter to the House Intelligence Committee, Atkinson said that he and Maguire were \"at an impasse\"<ref name=\"Cohen\"/> and wrote that \"As it now stands, my unresolved differences with the Acting DNI are affecting the execution of two of my most important duties and responsibilities\" (to whistleblowers and to Congress).<ref name=\"BertrandLippman\"/> The Trump administration eventually released the complaint<ref name=\"WapoComplaintReleased\"/><ref name=\"NYTComplaintReleased\"/> following demands for its release from the Senate<ref>{{cite magazine |first=Matt |last=Stieb |url=https://nymag.com/intelligencer/2019/09/senate-demands-trump-stop-blocking-whistleblower-complaint.html |title=Senate Passes Unanimous Resolution to Hand Whistle-blower Complaint to Intel Committees |magazine=[[New York (magazine)|New York]] |date=September 24, 2019}}</ref> and House.<ref>{{cite news |first=Brandi |last=Buchman |url=https://www.courthousenews.com/house-rebukes-trump-for-blocking-whistleblower-complaint/ |title=House Demands Trump Release Whistleblower Complaint |agency=[[Courthouse News Service]] |date=September 25, 2019}}</ref> The complaint prompted the launch of a House [[Impeachment inquiry against Donald Trump|impeachment inquiry against Trump]].<ref>{{cite news |first1=Nicholas |last1=Fandos |first2=Sheryl Gay |last2=Stolberg |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/27/us/politics/house-democrats-impeachment-trump.html |title=House Democrats Issue First Subpoena in Impeachment Inquiry |newspaper=The New York Times |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> The whistleblower complaint brought public attention to Atkinson, who previously was a little-known official.<ref name=\"Cohen\"/>\n\nIn mid-November, news reports revealed that the president was angry with the IG's perceived disloyalty and wanted to fire him.<ref>{{Cite news |first=Sonam |last=Sheth |date=November 12, 2019 |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/trump-wants-to-fire-the-intelligence-watchdog-who-told-congress-about-the-whistleblowers-complaint/ar-BBWF13G |title=Trump wants to fire the intelligence watchdog who told Congress about the whistleblower's complaint |work=[[Business Insider]] |via=[[MSN]] |access-date=November 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/12/us/politics/trump-michael-atkinson-inspector-general.html |title=Trump Has Considered Firing Intelligence Community Inspector General |last=Haberman |first=Maggie |date=November 12, 2019 |work=The New York Times |access-date=November 13, 2019 |last2=Schmidt |first2=Michael S. |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/two-gop-senators-warn-trump-against-firing-intel-committee-inspector-general-i-would-oppose-1471348 |title=Two GOP senators warn Trump against firing Intel Committee Inspector General: \"I would oppose\" |last=Zhao |first=Christina |date=November 12, 2019 |work=[[Newsweek]] |language=en |access-date=November 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rawstory.com/2019/11/trump-trying-to-fire-inspector-general-is-a-confession-he-did-something-criminal-nicolle-wallace/ |title=Trump trying to fire inspector general is a confession he 'did something criminal': Nicolle Wallace |last=Brigham |first=Bob |website=[[The Raw Story]] |language=en-US |access-date=November 13, 2019 |date=November 12, 2019}}</ref> He was dismissed by President Trump on April 3, 2020.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==See also==\n*[[Presidency of Donald Trump]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n*[https://www.congress.gov/115/chrg/CHRG-115shrg29479/CHRG-115shrg29479.pdf Senate Select Committee on Intelligence Questionnaire (Page 92)] {{PD-notice}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Atkinson, Michael}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American lawyers]]\n[[Category:Cornell Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Oswego, New York]]\n[[Category:People from Pulaski, New York]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University alumni]]\n[[Category:Trump administration personnel]]\n[[Category:United States Department of Justice officials]]\n[[Category:United States Inspectors General]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American intelligence official}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n|name        = Michael Atkinson\n|image       = Michael K. Atkinson official photo.jpg\n|office      = [[Inspector General of the Intelligence Community]]\n|president   = [[Donald Trump]]\n|term_start  = May 17, 2018<br/>On leave: April 3, 2020 \u2013 present<!-- May 3, 2020 -->\n|term_end    = <!-- May 3, 2020 -->\n|predecessor = Charles McCullough\n|successor   = Thomas Monheim (acting)\n|birth_name  = Michael Kevin Atkinson\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1964|5|16}}\n|birth_place = [[Oswego, New York]], U.S.\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|spouse      = Kathryn Cameron\n|education   = [[Syracuse University]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]])<br/>[[Cornell University]] ([[Juris Doctor|JD]])\n}}\n'''Michael Kevin Atkinson''' (born May 16, 1964) is an American attorney. He worked for the [[United States Department of Justice]] for approximately 15 years, before becoming the second [[Inspector General of the Intelligence Community]]. He assumed office on May 17, 2018.\n\nAtkinson is known for alerting Congress in September 2019 to a whistleblower complaint about President [[Donald Trump]] pressuring Ukraine to investigate [[2020 United States presidential election|political rival for the presidency]] Democrat [[Joe Biden]] and his son [[Hunter Biden]]; [[Trump\u2013Ukraine scandal|the scandal]] eventually led to [[Impeachment of Donald Trump|Trump's impeachment]] and acquittal.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nOn April 3, 2020, President Trump dismissed Atkinson, saying he \"no longer\" had confidence in the Inspector General. Atkinson will be removed from his office in 30 days, as outlined in a letter sent from Trump to the Senate Intelligence Committee on April 3.<ref name=\":0\">{{cite news |first1=Natasha |last1=Bertrand |first2=Andrew |last2=Desiderio |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/03/trump-fires-intelligence-community-inspector-general-164287 |title=Trump fires intelligence community inspector general who defied him on Ukraine |website=[[Politico]] |language=en |access-date=2020-04-04 |date=2020-04-03}}</ref> He was put on administrative leave immediately after the letter's publication.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/04/chuck-grassley-intel-community-watchdog-firing-164831 |title=Trump Defends Firing \u2018Terrible\u2019 Intel Community Watchdog as Republicans Question Sacking |work=[[Politico]] |language=en-US |accessdate=April 5, 2020 |date=April 4, 2020}}</ref>  A bipartisan group of senators demanded a more thorough explanation from Trump regarding the ousting.<ref>https://www.cbsnews.com/news/senators-demand-more-information-from-trump-on-ousting-of-intel-community-inspector-general</ref><ref>https://www.politico.com/news/2020/04/10/barr-russia-trump-durham-178690</ref><ref>https://www.deseret.com/utah/2020/4/9/21215155/donald-trump-coronavirus-mitt-romney-inspector-general-firing</ref>\n\n==Early life==\nAtkinson was born in [[Oswego, New York]], and was raised in [[Pulaski, New York]].<ref name=\"SenQuestion\">{{cite web |title=Response to Questionnaire for Completion by Presidential Nominees |url=https://www.intelligence.senate.gov/sites/default/files/documents/q-matkinson-011718.pdf |publisher=United States Senate |accessdate=September 20, 2019}}</ref> He graduated from Pulaski Academy and Central School in 1982<ref>{{cite news |first=Mark |last=Weiner |url=https://www.syracuse.com/politics/2019/09/inspector-general-who-received-trump-complaint-is-pulaski-native-syracuse-grad.html |title=Inspector General who received Trump complaint is Pulaski native, Syracuse grad |newspaper=[[The Post-Standard]] |location=[[Syracuse, New York]] |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> and earned his [[Bachelor of Arts]] from [[Syracuse University]] in 1986 and his [[Juris Doctor]] from [[Cornell Law School]] in 1991.<ref name=\"SenQuestion\" />\n\n==Career==\n===Legal career in private practice and the Justice Department===\nAfter graduating from law school, Atkinson was admitted to the District of Columbia Bar,<ref name=\"DCBar\">{{cite web |title=Find members |url=https://join.dcbar.org/eweb/DynamicPage.aspx?Site=dcbar&WebCode=FindMember |publisher=[[District of Columbia Bar]] |accessdate=September 20, 2019}}</ref> and joined the law firm of [[Winston & Strawn]], where he worked for 11 years, first as an associate and then as a partner.<ref name=\"ConfirmationStatement\">{{cite web |url=https://www.intelligence.senate.gov/sites/default/files/documents/os-matkinson-011718.pdf |title=Statement of Michael K. Atkinson, Nominee for Inspector General of the Intelligence Community before the United States Senate Select Committee on Intelligence |date=January 17, 2018 |publisher=United States Senate}}</ref>\n\nAfter the [[September 11 attacks]], Atkinson decided to enter public service, and worked for the U.S. Department of Justice for 15 years. He was a trial attorney in the [[United States Department of Justice Criminal Division|Justice Department's Criminal Division]], Fraud Section, from 2002 through 2006 and [[Assistant United States Attorney|Assistant U.S. Attorney]] in the [[United States Attorney for the District of Columbia|U.S. Attorney's Office for the District of Columbia]] from 2006 through 2016.<ref name=\"ConfirmationStatement\"/> Atkinson then moved to the [[United States Department of Justice National Security Division|Justice Department's National Security Division]].<ref name=\"ConfirmationStatement\"/><ref name=\"Cohen\">{{cite news |first=Zachary |last=Cohen |url=https://www.cnn.com/2019/09/23/politics/ic-ig-michael-atkinson-whistleblower-complaint/index.html |title=Whistleblower controversy thrusts little-known Trump appointee into the limelight |work=[[CNN]] |date=September 23, 2019}}</ref>\n\nMajor cases on which Atkinson worked while in the Justice Department included the prosecution of former [[United States House of Representatives|U.S. Representative]] [[William J. Jefferson]] on corruption charges (of which Jefferson was convicted) and the campaign finance investigation into [[Mayor of the District of Columbia|D.C. Mayor]] [[Vincent C. Gray]] (which was closed in 2015 without charges being brought). Atkinson received the Attorney General's Award for Distinguished Service for his work on the Jefferson case.<ref>{{cite news |first=Morgan |last=Chalfant |url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/463115-meet-the-trump-appointed-ig-at-center-of-whistleblower-drama |title=Meet the Trump-appointed IG at center of whistleblower drama |work=[[The Hill (newspaper)|The Hill]] |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Inspector General of the Intelligence Community===\n{{Further|Trump\u2013Ukraine scandal}}{{Trump\u2013Ukraine scandal}}\nAtkinson became [[Inspector General of the Intelligence Community]] (ICIG) in May 2018.<ref name=\"SenQuestion\" /> He was nominated to the position in November 2017 by President [[Donald Trump]]<ref>{{cite news |first=Debra J. |last=Groom |url=https://www.nny360.com/news/trump-nominates-pulaski-grad-to-intelligence-post/article_57315ce4-d954-52b0-b24d-8a2215946980.html |title=Trump nominates Pulaski grad to intelligence post |newspaper=[[Watertown Daily Times]] |date=November 12, 2017}}</ref> and was confirmed by the [[United States Senate]] by [[voice vote]] on May 14, 2018.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.congress.gov/nomination/115th-congress/1252 |title=PN1252 \u2014 Michael K. Atkinson \u2014 Office of the Director of National Intelligence, 115th Congress (2017-2018) |website=[[Congress.gov]]}}</ref> At his confirmation hearings, Atkinson indicated that he would bring order to the troubled ICIG's office, which had a reputation for dysfunction, and pledged to revive a whistleblower program that had become virtually defunct under the previous Acting Inspector General,<ref name=\"BertrandLippman\">{{cite news |first1=Natasha |last1=Bertrand |first2=Daniel |last2=Lippman |url=https://www.politico.com/story/2019/09/23/atkinson-trump-ukraine-whistleblower-scandal-1508594 |title=The intelligence watchdog at the center of Ukraine firestorm |work=Politico |date=September 23, 2019}}</ref> saying that he would \"encourage, operate, and enforce a program for authorized disclosures by whistleblowers within the intelligence community that validates moral courage without compromising national security and without retaliation.\"<ref name=\"ConfirmationStatement\"/> Restoring the whistleblower program was a major priority among members of the [[Senate Intelligence Committee]].<ref name=\"BertrandLippman\"/>\n\nIn August 2019, Atkinson, as inspector general, received a formal complaint from a whistleblower within the [[U.S. Intelligence Community]] who stated that they had learned, in the course of normal duties, that Trump had [[Abuse of power|abused his power]] \"to solicit [[Foreign interference in the 2020 United States elections|interference from a foreign country in the 2020 U.S. election]],\" specifically by pressuring a foreign government ([[Ukraine]]) to investigate former Vice President Joe Biden and his son Hunter Biden.<ref name=\"WapoComplaintReleased\">{{cite news |first=Devlin |last=Barrett |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/house-intelligence-committee-releases-whistleblowers-complaint-citing-trumps-call-with-ukraines-president/2019/09/26/402052ee-e056-11e9-be96-6adb81821e90_story.html |title=Whistleblower claimed Trump abused his office and that White House officials tried to cover it up |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref><ref name=\"NYTComplaintReleased\">{{cite news |first=Eileen |last=Sullivan |authorlink=Eileen Sullivan |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/26/us/politics/whistleblower-complaint-released.html |title=Whistle-Blower's Complaint Says White House Tried to 'Lock Down' Ukraine Call Records |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=September 26, 2019}}</ref> The whistleblower, a [[Central Intelligence Agency]] (CIA) officer detailed to the White House,<ref name=\"Detailed\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/26/us/politics/who-is-whistleblower.html |title=Whistle-Blower Is a C.I.A. Officer Who Was Detailed to the White House |first1=Adam |last1=Goldman |first2=Michael S. |last2=Schmidt |first3=Julian E. |last3=Barnes |date=September 26, 2019 |newspaper=The New York Times |authorlink1=Adam Goldman |authorlink2=Michael S. Schmidt}}</ref> submitted the report to Atkinson under the provisions of the [[Intelligence Community Whistleblower Protection Act]] (ICWPA).<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.justsecurity.org/66211/qa-on-whistleblower-complaint-being-withheld-from-congressional-intelligence-committees/ |title=Q&A on Whistleblower Complaint Being Withheld from Congressional Intelligence Committees |work=[[Just Security]] |date=September 17, 2019 |first=Kel |last=McClanahan}}</ref> \n\nAtkinson looked into the complaint, and interviewed several government officials whom the whistleblower identified as having information to substantiate his claims.<ref name=\"Detailed\"/> On August 26, having found the complaint to be both \"credible\" and \"of urgent concern\" (as defined by the ICWPA), Atkinson transmitted the complaint to [[Joseph Maguire]], the acting [[Director of National Intelligence]] (DNI).<ref>{{Cite web |first=Margaret |last=Taylor |date=September 17, 2019 |url=https://www.lawfareblog.com/mysterious-whistleblower-complaint-what-adam-schiff-talking-about |title=The Mysterious Whistleblower Complaint: What Is Adam Schiff Talking About? |work=[[Lawfare (blog)|Lawfare]]}}</ref> Under ICWPA, the DNI \"shall\" forward a complaint deemed credible and of urgent concern, within seven days of receipt, to the [[Senate Intelligence Committee|Senate]] and [[House Intelligence Committee]]s. The Trump administration, however, withheld the complaint from Congress; [[Steven Engel]] of the Justice Department's [[Office of Legal Counsel]] issued a determination saying that the acting DNI did not need to give the complaint to Congress because, in the opinion of the OLC, the complaint was not related to \"an intelligence activity\" under the acting DNI's authority.<ref>{{cite web |first=Jacob |last=Schulz |url=https://www.lawfareblog.com/olc-issues-opinion-about-urgent-concern-determination-whistleblower-complain-dni |title=OLC Issues an Opinion About the \"Urgent Concern\" Determination on the Whistleblower Complaint by the DNI |work=Lawfare |date=September 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |first1=Matt |last1=Zapotosky |first2=Devlin |last2=Barrett |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national-security/justice-dept-rejected-investigation-of-trump-phone-call-just-weeks-after-it-began-examining-the-matter/2019/09/25/6f7977ce-dfb5-11e9-8dc8-498eabc129a0_story.html |title=Justice Dept. rejected investigation of Trump phone call just weeks after it began examining the matter |newspaper=The Washington Post |date=September 25, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Engle |first1=Steven |title=\"Urgent Concern\" Determination by the Inspector General of the Intelligence Community |url=https://www.justice.gov/olc/file/1204586/download |website=justice.gov |publisher=[[United States Department of Justice]] |accessdate=September 28, 2019}}</ref>\n\nClashing with Maguire,<ref name=\"Cohen\"/> Atkinson himself notified Congress about the existence of the whistleblower report.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://thehill.com/policy/national-security/462464-timeline-the-trump-whistleblower-complaint |title=Timeline: The Trump whistleblower complaint |last=Bowden |first=John |date=September 21, 2019 |work=The Hill |accessdate=September 23, 2019}}</ref> In a letter to the House Intelligence Committee, Atkinson said that he and Maguire were \"at an impasse\"<ref name=\"Cohen\"/> and wrote that \"As it now stands, my unresolved differences with the Acting DNI are affecting the execution of two of my most important duties and responsibilities\" (to whistleblowers and to Congress).<ref name=\"BertrandLippman\"/> The Trump administration eventually released the complaint<ref name=\"WapoComplaintReleased\"/><ref name=\"NYTComplaintReleased\"/> following demands for its release from the Senate<ref>{{cite magazine |first=Matt |last=Stieb |url=https://nymag.com/intelligencer/2019/09/senate-demands-trump-stop-blocking-whistleblower-complaint.html |title=Senate Passes Unanimous Resolution to Hand Whistle-blower Complaint to Intel Committees |magazine=[[New York (magazine)|New York]] |date=September 24, 2019}}</ref> and House.<ref>{{cite news |first=Brandi |last=Buchman |url=https://www.courthousenews.com/house-rebukes-trump-for-blocking-whistleblower-complaint/ |title=House Demands Trump Release Whistleblower Complaint |agency=[[Courthouse News Service]] |date=September 25, 2019}}</ref> The complaint prompted the launch of a House [[Impeachment inquiry against Donald Trump|impeachment inquiry against Trump]].<ref>{{cite news |first1=Nicholas |last1=Fandos |first2=Sheryl Gay |last2=Stolberg |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/09/27/us/politics/house-democrats-impeachment-trump.html |title=House Democrats Issue First Subpoena in Impeachment Inquiry |newspaper=The New York Times |date=September 27, 2019}}</ref> The whistleblower complaint brought public attention to Atkinson, who previously was a little-known official.<ref name=\"Cohen\"/>\n\nIn mid-November, news reports revealed that the president was angry with the IG's perceived disloyalty and wanted to fire him.<ref>{{Cite news |first=Sonam |last=Sheth |date=November 12, 2019 |url=https://www.msn.com/en-us/news/politics/trump-wants-to-fire-the-intelligence-watchdog-who-told-congress-about-the-whistleblowers-complaint/ar-BBWF13G |title=Trump wants to fire the intelligence watchdog who told Congress about the whistleblower's complaint |work=[[Business Insider]] |via=[[MSN]] |access-date=November 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/11/12/us/politics/trump-michael-atkinson-inspector-general.html |title=Trump Has Considered Firing Intelligence Community Inspector General |last=Haberman |first=Maggie |date=November 12, 2019 |work=The New York Times |access-date=November 13, 2019 |last2=Schmidt |first2=Michael S. |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.newsweek.com/two-gop-senators-warn-trump-against-firing-intel-committee-inspector-general-i-would-oppose-1471348 |title=Two GOP senators warn Trump against firing Intel Committee Inspector General: \"I would oppose\" |last=Zhao |first=Christina |date=November 12, 2019 |work=[[Newsweek]] |language=en |access-date=November 13, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.rawstory.com/2019/11/trump-trying-to-fire-inspector-general-is-a-confession-he-did-something-criminal-nicolle-wallace/ |title=Trump trying to fire inspector general is a confession he 'did something criminal': Nicolle Wallace |last=Brigham |first=Bob |website=[[The Raw Story]] |language=en-US |access-date=November 13, 2019 |date=November 12, 2019}}</ref> He was dismissed by President Trump on April 3, 2020.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\n==See also==\n*[[Presidency of Donald Trump]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n*[https://www.congress.gov/115/chrg/CHRG-115shrg29479/CHRG-115shrg29479.pdf Senate Select Committee on Intelligence Questionnaire (Page 92)] {{PD-notice}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Atkinson, Michael}}\n[[Category:1964 births]]\n[[Category:21st-century American lawyers]]\n[[Category:Cornell Law School alumni]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Oswego, New York]]\n[[Category:People from Pulaski, New York]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University alumni]]\n[[Category:Trump administration personnel]]\n[[Category:United States Department of Justice officials]]\n[[Category:United States Inspectors General]]\n", "name_user": "95.144.190.215", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Michael_Atkinson_(Inspector_General)"}
{"title_page": "Anbe Sivam", "text_new": "{{short description|2003 film by Sundar C.}}\n{{featured article}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Anbe Sivam\n| image          = Anbe Sivam.jpg\n| alt            = Poster featuring Kamal Haasan (\"left\") and {{nbsp}}Madhavan (\"right\")\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Sundar C.]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* K. Muralitharan\n* V. Swaminathan\n* G. Venugopal\n* Sundar C.\n}}\n| writer         = {{plainlist|\n* [[Kamal Haasan]]\n}}\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* Kamal Haasan\n* [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]\n* [[Kiran Rathod]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cinematography = [[Arthur A. Wilson]]\n| editing        = [[P. Sai Suresh]]\n| studio         = [[Lakshmi Movie Makers]]\n| distributor    = Lakshmi Movie Makers\n| released       = {{Film date|2003|01|15|df=y}}<ref name=\"ASBBFC\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/anbea-sivam-1970 |title=Anbea Sivam (12A) |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517052505/http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/anbea-sivam-1970 |archive-date=17 May 2016 |access-date=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n| runtime        = 160 minutes<ref name=\"Panorama\">{{Cite web |url=http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/FrmIP2003Award.aspx?PdfName=IP2003.pdf |title=2003 Indian Panorama |publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]] |format=PDF |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328100714/http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/FrmIP2003Award.aspx?PdfName=IP2003.pdf |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = [[Indian rupee sign|{{INR}}]]120&nbsp;million<ref name=\"bg\">{{Cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/with-chandramukhi-tamil-superstar-rajnikant-revives-his-fading-career/1/193427.html |title=Return of the king |last=Ram |first=Arun |date=20 June 2005 |work=[[India Today]] |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140925135648/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/with-chandramukhi-tamil-superstar-rajnikant-revives-his-fading-career/1/193427.html |archive-date=25 September 2014}}</ref>{{efn|The average exchange rate in 2003 was 45.66 [[Indian rupee]]s ({{INR}}) per 1 US dollar (US$).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://inwww.rediff.com/business/slide-show/slide-show-1-rupee-vs-dollar-in-the-last-2-decades/20120518.htm?print=true |title=Rupee vs dollar: From 1990 to 2012 |date=18 May 2012 |website=[[Rediff.com]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321115240/http://inwww.rediff.com/business/slide-show/slide-show-1-rupee-vs-dollar-in-the-last-2-decades/20120518.htm?print=true |archive-date=21 March 2015 |access-date=31 March 2016}}</ref>|name=exchange2003}}\n}}\n\n'''''Anbe Sivam''''' ({{trans|Love is God}})<ref name=\"Swarajya1\">{{Cite web |url=https://swarajyamag.com/culture/anbe-sivam-misleading-title-that-matches-the-purpose |title=Anbe Sivam: Stairway To The Pseudo-Secular Heaven |last=Neelakandan |first=Aravindan |date=5 May 2017 |website=[[Swarajya (magazine)|Swarajya]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109154017/https://swarajyamag.com/culture/anbe-sivam-misleading-title-that-matches-the-purpose |archive-date=9 January 2018 |access-date=9 January 2018}}</ref> is a 2003 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[comedy-drama]] film directed and co-produced by [[Sundar C.]] with K. Muralitharan, V. Swaminathan and G. Venugopal under the banner of [[Lakshmi Movie Makers]]. The film was written by [[Kamal Haasan]], and [[Madhan (writer)|Madhan]] provided the dialogues. ''Anbe Sivam'' features Haasan, [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]] and [[Kiran Rathod]] in the lead roles, with [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]], [[Santhana Bharathi]], [[Seema (actress)|Seema]] and [[Uma Riyaz Khan]] playing supporting characters.\n\nThe film tells the story of an unexpected journey from [[Bhubaneswar]] to [[Chennai]] undertaken by two men of contrasting personalities, Nallasivam and Anbarasu. The musical score was composed by [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]. [[Arthur A. Wilson]] and M. Prabhaharan undertook responsibility for the film's cinematography and art direction, respectively.\n\nProduced on a budget of [[Indian rupee sign|{{INR}}]]120&nbsp;million, ''Anbe Sivam'' takes on several themes, including [[communism]], [[atheism]], and [[altruism]], and depicts Haasan's views as a [[Humanism|humanist]]. The film was released on 15 January 2003 to positive reviews from critics, but [[Box-office bomb|underperformed]] at the box office. Despite its failure, it gained recognition over the years through re-runs on television channels and is now regarded as a classic and a [[cult film]] in [[Tamil cinema]].\n\n''Anbe Sivam'' was screened as part of the Indian Panorama section of the [[International Film Festival of India]] in 2003. At the [[51st Filmfare Awards South]], it received a [[Filmfare Special Award&nbsp;\u2013 South|Special Jury Award]] and received nominations in the [[Filmfare Award for Best Film&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Film]] and [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Actor]] (Haasan) categories. Madhavan was awarded [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] at the 2003 [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]].It is the second highest rated movie on IMDB \n\n== Plot ==\nTwo men waiting for a flight to [[Chennai]] at the [[Biju Patnaik International Airport]] in [[Bhubaneswar]] engage in conversation. One is a [[commercial director]], Anbarasu, who prefers the abbreviated name A.{{nbsp}}Aras, and the other is a scarred and deformed socialist, Nallasivam, alias Nalla. When the flight is cancelled due to heavy rain, Aras initially suspects Nalla is a terrorist and informs the authorities, only to discover that he was mistaken. With the rain flooding the city, the two men are forced to share a room for the night. Both need to return to Chennai: Aras to be present at his wedding, and Nalla has to deliver a {{INR}}3,200,000{{efn|name=exchange2003}} cheque, recently awarded to him after he won a court case, to a group of union workers. After a traumatic night, and no hope for a flight, the two men take a bus to board the [[Coromandel Express]] train. Aras' bag gets stolen on the way leaving him with only his credit card, which no one accepts. Using his presence of mind, Nalla repeatedly bails Aras out of trouble while Aras tries escaping from him at every juncture, only to end up with him again. While waiting for the train at the [[Ichchapuram]] railway station, Nalla begins to tell Aras his story.\n\nA few years earlier, a healthy Nalla took part in various [[street theatre]] performances protesting against [[Foreign direct investment|multinational corporation-driven industrialisation]], that resulted in the marginalisation of the [[Workforce|labour force]]. He was at odds with Kandasamy Padayatchi, a manipulative factory owner who refused to give his workers a raise. Nalla satirically imitated Padayatchi in many of his shows. However, in an unexpected turn of events, Nalla and Padayatchi's daughter Balasaraswathi alias Bala, fell in love with each other. To avoid a potential conflict with Padayatchi, the two decided to elope to Kerala. Nalla boarded a bus bound for Kerala, and on his way to meet Bala, the bus crashed on a hillside leaving him scarred, disfigured, and partially paralysed for life. After recovering from his wounds, he visited Bala only to be informed by Padayatchi that his daughter was already married and has settled abroad. Padayatchi had earlier lied to Bala that Nalla died in the accident. It was also at this time that Nalla became a firm believer in kindness and love. Despite suffering from an inferiority complex due to his scarred and deformed body, Nalla performs community service and social work with renewed fervour while continuing to fight for union causes.\n\nUpon their arrival at Chennai, Aras delivers Nalla's cheque to the union workers. He invites Nalla to his wedding, where, to his utter astonishment, Nalla sees that Aras's bride is Bala. Padayatchi spots Nalla and asks him why he is at the wedding. He tells Padayatchi that he was invited by Aras, and later persuades him to sign the papers which will help Padayatchi's workers get a raise. To prevent the disruption of Bala's wedding and avoid damaging his own reputation, Padayatchi yields to Nalla's demands. After signing the papers, Padayatchi instructs his assistant to eliminate Nalla. However, his assistant has a change of heart as he is about to kill him. Padayatchi's assistant believes that the misdeeds he committed for Padayatchi resulted in the death of the assistant's daughter. Padayatchi's assistant requests Nalla to stay as far away from his boss as possible; Nalla assents and walks away.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{multiple image\n| direction = horizontal\n| width1    = 209\n| width2    = 200\n| footer    = [[Kamal Haasan]] and [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]] play the roles of Nallasivam and Anbarasu, respectively.\n| image1    = Kamal Haasan at 62nd Filmfare Awards south.jpg\n| alt1      = Kamal Haasan posing for the camera at the 62nd Filmfare Awards South ceremony\n| image2    = Madhavan Saala Khadoos (cropped).jpg\n| alt2      = Madhavan posing for the camera at the premiere of his 2016 film Saala Khadoos\n}}\n* [[Kamal Haasan]] as Nallasivam alias Nalla{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]] as Anbarasu alias A. Aras{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Kiran Rathod]] as Balasaraswathi alias Bala{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]] as Kandasamy Padayatchi{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Santhana Bharathi]] as Padayatchi's assistant{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Seema (actress)|Seema]] as Balasaraswathi's aunt{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Yugi Sethu]] as Uthaman<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2010/02/05/26/Ar02600.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=147160&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Content is king |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |date=5 February 2010 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410134013/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH%2F2010%2F02%2F05%2F26%2FAr02600.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=147160&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=10 April 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Uma Riyaz Khan]] as Mehrunissa{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 53:18 to 53:25}}<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/260417/not-just-a-star-wife-uma.html |title=Not just a star wife: Uma |last=Nair |first=Vidya |date=26 April 2017 |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |access-date=30 April 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170430160205/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/260417/not-just-a-star-wife-uma.html |archive-date=30 April 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Pasi Sathya]] as a tea stall owner<ref name=\"MRReview\" />\n* Sujatha Narayanan as a tea shop owner who helps Nallasivam<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/Expert-Juggler-of-Trades-Revels-in-Her-Bliss/2016/03/24/article3342669.ece |title=Expert Juggler of Trades Revels in Her Bliss |last=Chandni |first=U. |date=24 March 2016 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=31 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331080817/http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/Expert-Juggler-of-Trades-Revels-in-Her-Bliss/2016/03/24/article3342669.ece |archive-date=31 March 2016}}</ref>{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:44:05 to 1:46:25}} \n* [[Balu Anand]] as the train ticket checker for the Coromandel Express<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/actor-balu-anand-passes-away/article8686086.ece |title=Actor Balu Anand passes away |date=3 June 2016 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=6 June 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606145950/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/actor-balu-anand-passes-away/article8686086.ece |archive-date=6 June 2016}}</ref>{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:54:25 to 1:55:40}}\n* [[R. S. Shivaji]] as the Ichchapuram railway station master<ref name=\"MRReview\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:54:25 to 1:55:40}}\n* [[Ilavarasu]] as a police inspector and aide of Padayatchi<ref name=\"MRReview\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:17:22 to 1:19:34}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nAfter completing the draft for a film's script in early 2002, Kamal Haasan approached the [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] filmmaker [[Priyadarshan]] to direct it.<ref name=\"SWP\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/24priyan.htm |title=No regrets, no remakes |last=Warrier |first=Shobha |date=24 April 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325133257/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/24priyan.htm |archive-date=25 March 2016 |access-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> The two men were keen to work together since the late 1990s, and upon reading the script, Priyadarshan believed that it had the potential to be an \"emotional love story\".<ref name=\"SWP\" /> The film's title ''Anbe Sivam'' was derived from the [[Shaivism|Shaivite]] saint [[Tirumular]]'s poem ''[[Tirumantiram]]''.<ref name=\"SRAKMR\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/03/29/stories/2002032901230300.htm |title=The long and short of it... |last=Kumar |first=S. R. Ashok |date=29 March 2002 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326092025/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/03/29/stories/2002032901230300.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |last2=Rangarajan |first2=Malathi}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2002, Priyadarshan opted out of the project owing to creative differences.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/jun/14priyan.htm |title=Priyadarshan out of Kamal's film |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |authorlink=Subhash K. Jha |date=14 June 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325143149/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/jun/14priyan.htm |archive-date=25 March 2016 |access-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> He was replaced by [[Sundar C.]], who agreed to produce the film as well.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/its-all-fun-and-frolic/article3387502.ece |title=It's all fun and frolic |last=Manigandan |first=K. R. |date=5 May 2012 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328075229/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/its-all-fun-and-frolic/article3387502.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> ''Anbe Sivam'' was co-produced and distributed by Swaminathan, K.{{nbsp}}Muralitharan and G.{{nbsp}}Venugopal under the production banner of [[Lakshmi Movie Makers]].{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}<ref name=\"BH\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/64853/Anbe%20Sivam |title=Anbe Sivam |website=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517023623/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/64853/Anbe%20Sivam |archive-date=17 May 2016 |access-date=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Cast and crew ===\nIn addition to being the film's writer, Haasan also played the central character. Madhavan was selected to play the film's second lead in January 2002.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/jan/19kamal.htm |title=Kamal, Madhavan: Boys just wanna have fun |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=19 January 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325142732/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/jan/19kamal.htm |archive-date=25 March 2016 |access-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> According to Kiran Rathod, she received a phone call from Haasan's office informing her that she was offered the role of Balasaraswathi, which she accepted.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/how-i-met-kamal-haasan/article6570994.ece |title=How I met Kamal Haasan |last=Ramanujam |first=Srinivasa |date=6 November 2014 |work=The Hindu |access-date=25 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325141010/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/how-i-met-kamal-haasan/article6570994.ece |archive-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> Rathod's voice in the film was dubbed by the singer [[Anuradha Sriram]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Repository/getFiles.asp?Style=OliveXLib:LowLevelEntityToPrintGifMSIE_PASTISSUES2&Type=text/html&Locale=english-skin-custom&Path=TOICH/2011/04/23&ChunkNum=0&ID=Ar03005 |title=Did You Know? |date=23 April 2011 |work=The Times of India |access-date=8 January 2018 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180108102952/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Repository/getFiles.asp?Style=OliveXLib%3ALowLevelEntityToPrintGifMSIE_PASTISSUES2&Type=text%2Fhtml&Locale=english-skin-custom&Path=TOICH%2F2011%2F04%2F23&ChunkNum=0&ID=Ar03005 |archive-date=8 January 2018 |location=Chennai |page=30}}</ref> Uma Riyaz Khan played the role of Kamal's friend and professional colleague, Mehrunissa.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://archives.deccanchronicle.com/130530/entertainment-kollywood/article/mommy-rocks |title=This mommy rocks! |last=Das |first=Papri |date=30 May 2013 |work=Deccan Chronicle |access-date=25 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150619114816/http://archives.deccanchronicle.com/130530/entertainment-kollywood/article/mommy-rocks |archive-date=19 June 2015}}</ref> In a 2019 interview with ''[[The Indian Express]]'', the film's script assistant and costume designer, Sujatha Narayanan, revealed that [[Nandita Das]] and [[Shobana]] were the original choices for Balasaraswathi and Mehrunissa respectively and that both of them declined due to schedule conflicts.<ref name=\"AS16\">{{Cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/what-makes-kamal-haasan-anbe-sivam-a-timeless-classic-5540160/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/what-makes-kamal-haasan-anbe-sivam-a-timeless-classic-5540160/ |title=What makes Kamal Haasan\u2019s Anbe Sivam a timeless classic |last=Subhakeerthana |first=S. |date=15 January 2019 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |access-date=29 March 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329053429/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/what-makes-kamal-haasan-anbe-sivam-a-timeless-classic-5540160/ |archive-date=29 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote|text = He [Kamal] came over to me and said, 'Madhavan, I have seen some of your work and they were good.' [...] Then he continued, 'I have something for you. We should catch up!' [...] that was how ''Anbe Sivam'' happened.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/may/30maddy.htm |title=After Anbe Sivam, I became a hardcore Kamal fan |last=Warrier |first=Shobha |date=30 May 2008 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326021810/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/may/30maddy.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=26 March 2016}}</ref>|author = Madhavan on how he was cast in ''Anbe Sivam''|width = 35%|align = right}}\n\nThe actors Nassar and Santhana Bharathi played the roles of Kandasamy Padaiyatchi and his assistant, respectively, while cartoonist [[Madhan (writer)|Madhan]] featured in a cameo appearance as himself in addition to writing the film's dialogues.<ref name=\"BH\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 50:35 to 56:45}} In an interview with S.{{nbsp}}R. Ashok Kumar of ''[[The Hindu]]'' in 2006, Bharathi considered both ''Anbe Sivam'' and ''[[Michael Madana Kama Rajan]]'' (1990) to be the favourite roles of his career.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/this-character-artists-first-love-is-direction/article3048491.ece |title=This character artist's first love is direction |last=Kumar |first=S. R. Ashok |date=16 November 2006 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328064501/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/this-character-artists-first-love-is-direction/article3048491.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Arthur A. Wilson]], [[M. Prabhaharan]] and [[P. Sai Suresh]] handled the film's cinematography, art direction and editing, respectively.{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}<ref name=\"MRReview\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701310200.htm |title=Anbe Sivam |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |date=17 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326075815/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701310200.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref> [[Brinda (choreographer)|Brinda]], [[Chinni Prakash]] and [[Dinesh Kumar (choreographer)|Dinesh Kumar]] were in charge of the choreography while the stunt sequences were co-ordinated by [[Vikram Dharma]].<ref name=\"SRAK\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/10/stories/2003011001100200.htm |title=Films add glamour to harvest festival |last=Kumar |first=S. R. Ashok |date=10 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326081244/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/10/stories/2003011001100200.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cinemaexpress.com/cinemaexpress/story.aspx?Title=%E0%AE%86%E0%AE%9F%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9F+%E0%AE%A8%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%AF%E0%AE%95%E0%AE%A9%E0%AF%8D!&artid=112043&SectionID=144&MainSectionID=144&SectionName=Fashion&SEO= |title=\u0b86\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd! |last=\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd |first=\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbf |website=[[Cinema Express]] |language=Tamil |trans-title=King of Dance! |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20160909091120/http://web.archive.org/web/20160328094215/http://www.cinemaexpress.com/cinemaexpress/story.aspx?Title=%E0%AE%86%E0%AE%9F\u0bcd\u0b9f+\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd!&artid=112043&SectionID=144&MainSectionID=144&SectionName=Fashion&SEO= |archive-date=9 September 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Muthulakshmi Varadhan, Bharathi's sister-in-law, worked as an assistant editor in the film.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2012/03/08/26/Ar02600.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=451459&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Meet The Path-Breakers |last=Suresh |first=Sunayana |date=8 March 2012 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410081243/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH%2F2012%2F03%2F08%2F26%2FAr02600.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=451459&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=10 April 2016 |last2=Ramanujam |first2=Srinivasa |last3=Bharathan |first3=Bijoy |last4=Lakshmi |first4=V. |last5=Panikker |first5=Rohit |last6=Abudul Kareem |first6=Rehan}}</ref> The make-up for Haasan's scars was designed by [[Michael Westmore]] and Anil Premkarikar.<ref name=\"SRAK\" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/10/15/stories/2004101502460500.htm |title=From Texas to tinsel town |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |date=15 October 2004 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328085847/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/10/15/stories/2004101502460500.htm |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> In May 2002, Haasan completed the makeup for his character Nallasivam in Los Angeles after filming the song sequences for ''[[Panchathantiram]]'' (2002).<ref name=\"SRAKMR\" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/05/03/stories/2002050300320300.htm |title=Harrowing time in Toronto |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=3 May 2002 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326092734/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/05/03/stories/2002050300320300.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/30kamal.htm |title=What it means to be Kamal Haasan |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=30 April 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326093732/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/30kamal.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=26 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] for ''Anbe Sivam'' commenced in July 2002.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/jul/16kamal.htm |title='I'm working to clear debts' |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=16 July 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325143520/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/jul/16kamal.htm |archive-date=25 March 2016 |access-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> The first scene featuring the lead actors was shot at [[Pollachi Junction railway station]]. Haasan and Madhavan interacted closely during the initial stages of the shoot to ensure that the on-screen chemistry between the pair was apparent.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/sep/23kamal.htm |title=Facing the camera with The Legend |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=23 September 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326014654/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/sep/23kamal.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=26 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n''Anbe Sivam'' was shot on a restricted budget of {{INR}}120&nbsp;million, with the train and bus disaster sequences involving the use of settings and [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]].<ref name=\"bg\" />{{efn|name=exchange2003}} Madhavan, who began shooting his portions in September 2002,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/sep/20mad.htm |title='It's an out-and-out Madhavan film!' |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=20 September 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170106105356/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/sep/20mad.htm |archive-date=6 January 2017 |access-date=6 January 2017}}</ref> stated the film was shot in relatively empty locations.<ref name=\"SKJRediff\">{{Cite web |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/09kamal.htm |title=Kamal Haasan and Madhavan on their film Anbesivam |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=9 January 2003 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326014635/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/09kamal.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=11 June 2013}}</ref> The flood scenes set in [[Odisha]] were re-created with outdoor sets consisting of city roads submerged under water erected in the Odisha-[[Andhra Pradesh]] border.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOIM/2005/03/29/36/Ar03600.xml&CollName=TOI_MUMBAI_ARCHIVE&DOCID=434728&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Tsunami Premonitions |date=29 March 2005 |work=The Times of India |access-date=11 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411073938/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOIM%2F2005%2F03%2F29%2F36%2FAr03600.xml&CollName=TOI_MUMBAI_ARCHIVE&DOCID=434728&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=11 April 2016}}</ref> Filming also took place in Chennai, [[Visakhapatnam]] and on the [[Tamil Nadu]]-[[Karnataka]] border.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/01/14/stories/2003011400390400.htm |title=Madhavan makes his move |last=Rajamani |first=Radhika |date=14 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326014557/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/01/14/stories/2003011400390400.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref> The pre-climax scenes were filmed in what was then known as the [[Campa Cola]] compound in Guindy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2016/nov/06/what-you-learn-just-by-watching-kamal-haasan-1535684.html |title=What you learn just by watching Kamal Haasan |last=Narayanan |first=Sujatha |date=6 November 2016 |website=The New Indian Express |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161108142018/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2016/nov/06/what-you-learn-just-by-watching-kamal-haasan-1535684.html |archive-date=8 November 2016 |access-date=8 November 2016}}</ref> The climax scenes were filmed in a single take.<ref name=\"AS16\" />\n\n== Themes and influences ==\n''Anbe Sivam'' follows the events of a journey from Bhubaneswar to Chennai undertaken by two men of contrasting personalities, Nallasivam (Haasan), a physically challenged and witty socialist, and Anbarasu (Madhavan), a commercial director who supports [[capitalism]] and [[Globalization|globalisation]].<ref name=\"Pujaafive\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/my-five-r-pujaa/article5609403.ece |title=My five |last=Pujaa |first=R. |date=23 January 2014 |website=The Hindu |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326143212/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/my-five-r-pujaa/article5609403.ece |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=26 March 2016}}</ref> Due to unforeseen circumstances, the two are forced to undertake the journey together.<ref name=\"Sify Review\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-review-tamil-12525931.html |title=Anbe Sivam |website=[[Sify]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411181523/http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-review-tamil-12525931.html |archive-date=11 April 2014 |access-date=27 March 2016}}</ref> Throughout the narrative, a series of themes pertaining to [[communism]],{{efn|Nalla and Aras argue about the topics at the Ichchapuram railway station.{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:46:40 to 1:50:40}}|name=Topic}} compassion, globalisation,{{efn|name=Topic}} [[atheism]], and [[altruism]]{{efn|Aras donates blood to save a boy injured in a train accident from dying.{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 2:02:00 to 2:11:00}}}} are addressed; the film also showcases Haasan's views as a [[Humanism|humanist]].<ref name=\"Swarajya1\" /><ref name=\"Pujaafive\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/after-039ninaithale-inikkum039-kamal039s-039anbe-sivam039-may-get-a-re-release-507926 |title=After 'Ninaithale Inikkum', Haasan's 'Anbe Sivam' May Get a Re-Release |date=22 September 2013 |website=[[International Business Times]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327135713/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/after-039ninaithale-inikkum039-kamal039s-039anbe-sivam039-may-get-a-re-release-507926 |archive-date=27 March 2016 |access-date=27 March 2016}}</ref> According to Haasan, the characterisation of Nallasivam was inspired by the life of Communist playwright, actor, director, lyricist and theorist [[Safdar Hashmi]], who was chiefly associated with his work on [[street theatre]] in India.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2003/01/14/stories/2003011400910200.htm |title=No branding please... |last=Nayar |first=Mandira |date=14 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517020841/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2003/01/14/stories/2003011400910200.htm |archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref> Hashmi died on 2 January 1989 after being attacked by members of the [[Indian National Congress]] while staging a play, ''Halla Bol''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/drX89IpmCMTnyZpu5mowmM/Halla-Bol--Of-the-people-by-the-people.html |title=Halla Bol: Of the people, by the people |last=Ghosh |first=Tanushree |date=24 February 2014 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |access-date=17 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517021134/http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/drX89IpmCMTnyZpu5mowmM/Halla-Bol--Of-the-people-by-the-people.html |archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref> S.{{nbsp}}Anand of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' magazine notes that Haasan's views on humanism in the film also seemed to be inspired by those of [[Charlie Chaplin]].<ref name=\"Outlook\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/anbey-sivam-love-is-god/218710 |title=Anbey Sivam (Love is God) |last=Anand |first=S. |date=27 January 2003 |website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327131901/http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/anbey-sivam-love-is-god/218710 |archive-date=27 March 2016 |access-date=27 March 2016}}</ref> M. Kalyanaraman and Abdullah Nurullah of ''[[The Times of India]]'' opined that Nallasivam shared similar characteristics with street theatre artist Pralayan.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Is-Kamal-trending-lotus/articleshow/49824678.cms |title=Is Kamal trending lotus? |last=Kalyanaraman & Abdullah Nurullah |first=M. |date=18 November 2015 |work=The Times of India |access-date=6 June 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606135513/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Is-Kamal-trending-lotus/articleshow/49824678.cms |archive-date=6 June 2016 |last2=Nurullah |first2=Abdullah}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Kalyanaraman, ''Anbe Sivam'' proposes that man can make morally superior choices when he comes face to face with death. As a result, Haasan indicates that the belief of \"[[Shiva|Siva]] is love\" is the \"final stage of evolution of man into God\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/The-spiritual-Kamal-Hassan/articleshow/47204923.cms |title=The spiritual Kamal Hassan |last=Kalyanaraman |first=M. |date=8 May 2015 |website=The Times of India |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20161127164445/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/The-spiritual-Kamal-Hassan/articleshow/47204923.cms |archive-date=27 November 2016 |access-date=10 April 2016}}</ref> The film features a Tamil proverb from [[Manikkavacakar]]'s ''[[Tiruvacakam]]'', ''Tenn\u0101\u1e6du\u1e6daiya \u015aivan\u0113 p\u00f6\u1e5b\u1e5bi'' (\"Praise \u015aiva who resides in the ancient land and who belongs to all of humanity\"). Padayatchi utters this every time before he murders or assaults a person. Kalavai Venkat of ''[[Swarajya (magazine)|Swarajya]]'' magazine opined that Haasan had \"inappropriately used this harmonious sacred chant to demonize Hinduism.\"<ref name=\"Swarajya\">{{Cite web |url=http://swarajyamag.com/current-affairs/vishwaroopam-the-stark-reality-facing-the-hindus |title=Vishwaroopam: The Stark Reality Facing the Hindus |last=Venkat |first=Kalavai |date=5 February 2013 |website=Swarajya |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160805130528/http://swarajyamag.com/current-affairs/vishwaroopam-the-stark-reality-facing-the-hindus |archive-date=5 August 2016 |access-date=5 August 2016}}</ref>\n[[File:Palacio de Bellas Artes - Mural El Hombre in cruce de caminos Rivera 4.jpg|thumb|right|alt=Painting by Diego Rivera|Mexican painter [[Diego Rivera]]'s [[fresco]], ''[[Man at the Crossroads]]'' served as an inspiration for Nallasivam's painting to indicate the atrocities committed by Kandasamy Padayatchi.<ref name=\"NS\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/and-brahma-said/article1423679.ece |title=And, Brahma said... |last=Sivashankar |first=Nithya |date=28 August 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=27 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327120847/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/and-brahma-said/article1423679.ece |archive-date=27 March 2016}}</ref>]]\nThe film critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]], in his review of another Haasan film, ''[[Vishwaroopam]]'' (2013), found the ethnicity of the characters in the film to be a continuation of Haasan's inclusion of non-Tamil characters in his films. Rangan considered this to be Haasan's acknowledgement of the \"interconnectedness of the nation\" and \"the world beyond India\". He pointed out in his article that Haasan had experimented with the concept before by including the usage of [[Bengali language]] and meeting [[Bengalis]] in ''[[Mahanadi (film)|Mahanadi]]'' (1994), a [[Telugu language|Telugu-speaking]] love interest in ''[[Nammavar]]'' (1994), marrying a Bengali woman in ''[[Hey Ram]]'' (2000), conducting investigations with an [[Americans|American]] associate in ''[[Vettaiyaadu Vilaiyaadu (2006 film)|Vettaiyaadu Vilaiyaadu]]'' (2006), and marriage to a [[French people|Frenchwoman]] in ''[[Manmadan Ambu]]'' (2010). Rangan notes that in ''Anbe Sivam'', the inclusion of and interaction with the [[Odia people]] was another example of including non-Tamil characters in his films.<ref name=\"Rangan\">{{Cite web |url=https://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2003/03/02/anbe-sivam/ |title=Anbe Sivam |last=Rangan |first=Baradwaj |authorlink=Baradwaj Rangan |date=2 March 2003 |website=baradwajrangan.wordpress.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328061721/https://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2003/03/02/anbe-sivam/ |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/vishwaroopam-terror-messages/article4392667.ece |title=Vishwaroopam: Terror messages |last=Rangan |first=Baradwaj |date=8 February 2013 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331152158/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/vishwaroopam-terror-messages/article4392667.ece |archive-date=31 March 2016}}</ref> Rangan also compared Haasan's fight sequence with the use of an umbrella to the way he used a book and stool in ''[[Thoongathey Thambi Thoongathey]]'' (1983).<ref name=\"Rangan\" />\n\nAccording to a critic from [[Sify]], the basic plot of ''Anbe Sivam'' bears resemblance to the 1987 [[Road movie|road film]], ''[[Planes, Trains and Automobiles]]'' directed by [[John Hughes (filmmaker)|John Hughes]], which starred [[Steve Martin]] and [[John Candy]] in the lead roles. The critic noted Haasan and Madhavan's character share similar traits to that of the roles played by Candy and Martin in that film, respectively.<ref name=\"Sify Review\" /> The portrait painted by Nallasivam on the walls of Padayatchi's house is inspired by the Mexican painter [[Diego Rivera]]'s [[fresco]], ''[[Man at the Crossroads]]''.<ref name=\"NS\" /> The painting shows Nallasivam posing as Padayatchi's deity Shiva, the number 910 indicating the salary Padayatchi pays to his factory's workers, and the [[hammer and sickle]] communism symbol.<ref name=\"Swarajya1\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:09:40 to 1:11:20}} Aravindan Neelakandan from ''Swarajya'' commented on the influence of [[Marxism]] in the painting, believing it to be \"an empty vehicle to convey his ideology and is bereft of any intrinsic value in itself.\"<ref name=\"Swarajya1\" /> Srinivasa Ramanujam, writing for ''The Times of India'' in 2008, noted that the religious undertone in the film was similar to that of [[Rajinikanth]]'s ''[[Baba (2002 film)|Baba]]'' (2002).<ref name=\"Srinivasa Ramanujam 2008\">{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/An-avatar-in-his-own-right/articleshow/3123525.cms |title=An avatar in his own right |last=Ramanujam |first=Srinivasa |date=13 June 2008 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410082809/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/An-avatar-in-his-own-right/articleshow/3123525.cms |archive-date=10 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Music ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Anbe Sivam\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 11 December 2002\n| recorded     = 2002\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 35:16\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = Ayngaran Music<br/>An Ak Audio<br/>Hit Musics\n| producer     = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| prev_title   = [[Karmegham]]\n| prev_year    = 2002\n| next_title   = [[Anbu (2003 film)|Anbu]]\n| next_year    = 2003\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack album and background score for ''Anbe Sivam'' were composed by [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]], and the lyrics for the songs were written by [[Vairamuthu]] and [[P. Vijay]].<ref name=\"MR\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/the-unassailable-in-action/article2614700.ece |title=The unassailable in action! |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |date=10 November 2011 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331145155/http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/the-unassailable-in-action/article2614700.ece |archive-date=31 March 2016}}</ref> After composing the tune for the title song, Vidyasagar explained the situation of the song to Haasan, who wanted the song to be performed in such a way that the protagonist is singing according to the situation he finds himself in. Vidyasagar suggested that Haasan should sing the song himself to achieve the desired result, which the latter accepted.<ref name=\"SKJRediff\" /><ref name=\"SKJHindu\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701240300.htm |title=A thoroughly enjoyable experience |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=17 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326061156/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701240300.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref> The song \"Mouname Paarvayai\" was not included in the film.<ref name=\"MR\" /> The song \"Poovaasam\" is based on the ''Shuddh Sarang'' [[raga]].{{efn|According to singer [[Charulatha Mani]], the ''Shuddh Sarang'' raga closely resembles the [[Carnatic raga]], ''[[Hamsanadam]]''.<ref name=\"ARJCM\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/call-of-the-swan/article4368746.ece |title=Call of the swan |last=Mani |first=Charulatha |date=1 February 2013 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326053448/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/call-of-the-swan/article4368746.ece |archive-date=26 March 2016 |author-link=Charulatha Mani}}</ref>}} The male portions for the reprise of \"Poovaasam\" were sung by [[Sriram Parthasarathy]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/There-Can-Only-be-One-Ilaiyaraaja/2014/09/20/article2439914.ece |title=There Can Only be One Ilaiyaraaja |last=Subhakeerthana |first=S. |date=20 September 2014 |work=The New Indian Express |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326065007/http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/There-Can-Only-be-One-Ilaiyaraaja/2014/09/20/article2439914.ece |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref>{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:05:15 to 1:09:40}} while the original version was sung by [[Vijay Prakash]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/Vijay-Prakash-Turns-Mall-into-Concert-Hall/2015/11/03/article3110229.ece |title=Vijay Prakash Turns Mall into Concert Hall |date=3 November 2015 |work=The New Indian Express |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328070441/http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/Vijay-Prakash-Turns-Mall-into-Concert-Hall/2015/11/03/article3110229.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> [[Sadhana Sargam]] sang her portion of both versions of the song.{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:05:15 to 1:09:40}}<ref name=\"Saavn\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.saavn.com/s/album/tamil/Anbe-Sivam-2001/4VOtd-CCoP8_ |title=Anbe Sivam (2002)&nbsp;\u2013 Tracklist |website=[[Saavn]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105070518/http://www.saavn.com/s/album/tamil/Anbe-Sivam-2001/4VOtd-CCoP8_ |archive-date=5 January 2017 |access-date=5 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nMalathi Rangarajan of ''The Hindu'' wrote, \"Vidyasagar is scaling great heights as a composer. The theme song and the melodious {{sic|\"Pon Vaasam\"|nolink=y}} are pointers. Vairamuthu's lyrics deserve special mention here.\"<ref name=\"MRReview\" /> Singer [[Charulatha Mani]], in her column for ''The Hindu'', \"A Raga's Journey\", noted, \"Poovaasam\" possessed \"a charm that is born out of classicism incorporated in a populist piece\".<ref name=\"ARJCM\" /> Arkay of [[Rediff.com]] found the songs to be \"at best, okay\".<ref name=\"Rediff Review\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/16anbe.htm |title=Why would Haasan make himself so ugly? |last=Arkay |date=16 January 2003 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328120741/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/16anbe.htm |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> M. Suganth of ''The Times of India'', in his review for the music album, \"Lovers Special&nbsp;\u2013 Vol. 2\u20134\", included \"Poovaasam\" among the \"Hot Picks\" of the album.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2009/04/17/27/Ar02700.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=34477&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Lovers Special&nbsp;\u2013 Vol. 2\u20134 |last=Suganth |first=M. |date=17 April 2009 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105065709/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2009/04/17/27/Ar02700.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=34477&Keyword=(%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam)&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=5 January 2017}}</ref>\n{{clear}}\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 35:16\n| headline = Track-List\n| title1 = Anbe Sivam\n| extra1 = [[Kamal Haasan]], [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]]\n| lyrics1 = \n| length1 = 04:22\n| title2 = Elo Machi\n| extra2 = Kamal Haasan, [[Udit Narayan]]\n| lyrics2 = \n| length2 = 04:37\n| title3 = Mouname Paarvayai\n| extra3 = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], Chandrayee\n| lyrics3 = \n| length3 = 04:39\n| title5 = Naatukkoru Seithi\n| extra5 = Kamal Haasan, Chandran\n| lyrics5 = \n| length5 = 08:12\n| title4 = Poovaasam\n| extra4 = [[Vijay Prakash]], [[Sadhana Sargam]]\n| lyrics4 = \n| length4 = 04:30\n| title6 = Elo Machi\n| note6 = Reprise\n| extra6 = Udit Narayan, [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]]\n| lyrics6 = \n| length6 = 04:37\n| title7 = Poovaasam\n| note7 = Reprise\n| extra7 = [[Sriram Parthasarathy]], Sadhana Sargam\n| lyrics7 = \n| length7 = 04:25\n| all_writing = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| all_lyrics = [[Vairamuthu]], except the song \"Mouname Paarvayai\" was written by [[Pa. Vijay]]\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nAccording to S. R. Ashok Kumar of ''The Hindu'', the producers were confident that ''Anbe Sivam'' would be a strong competitor at the [[50th National Film Awards]] that they had the film reviewed by the [[Central Board of Film Certification]] before the end of 2002 so that they could enter the film into the annual awards list.<ref name=\"SRAK\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 00:00 to 00:03}} The film was released on 15 January 2003, which coincided with the [[Thai Pongal]] festival. It opened alongside five other films, including [[Vikram (actor)|Vikram]]'s ''[[Dhool]]'', [[Vijayakanth]]'s ''[[Chokka Thangam]]'', and ''[[Vaseegara (film)|Vaseegara]]'', which featured [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]].<ref name=\"ASBBFC\" /><ref name=\"SRAK\" />\n\n''Anbe Sivam'' was screened as a part of the Indian Panorama section of the [[International Film Festival of India]] in 2003.<ref name=\"Panorama\" /> As a tribute to Safdar Hashmi, a special preview of the film was organised by Haasan in association with Safdar Hashmi Memorial Trust (SAHMAT) on 9 January 2003 at [[Siri Fort Auditorium]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://archives.peoplesdemocracy.in/2003/0119/01192003_anbesivam.htm |title=Kamal Haasan Pays Tribute to Safdar Hashmi Anbe Sivam Film Preview Show Held By SAHMAT |date=19 January 2003 |work=[[People's Democracy (newspaper)|People's Democracy]] |access-date=17 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517025109/http://archives.peoplesdemocracy.in/2003/0119/01192003_anbesivam.htm |archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref> The film was dubbed into Telugu as ''Sathyame Sivam'' and released on 28 February 2003.<ref name=\"Jeevi\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-sathyamesivam.html |title=Sathyame Sivam |last=Jeevi |date=28 February 2003 |website=[[Idlebrain.com]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328120937/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-sathyamesivam.html |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> It was dubbed into Hindi as ''Shivam'' two years later in 2005. After the release of the original Tamil version, the dubbing rights for the Hindi version were sold at a low price, much to the irritation of the lead actors as they were not able to dub for themselves in Hindi.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-in-hindi-news-tamil-kkfv6gjbbhf.html |title='Anbe Sivam' in Hindi |date=7 April 2005 |website=Sify |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328122006/http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-in-hindi-news-tamil-kkfv6gjbbhf.html |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Critical response ===\nBaradwaj Rangan described the film as \"Kamal's latest solo attempt to bend, twist, shape-shift Tamil cinema into forms never-before seen.\"<ref name=\"Rangan\" /> In his review of the film's DVD, M. Suganth, writing for ''The Times of India'', called it \"one of the finest movies of the decade\" and praised the story, screenplay and dialogues before terming the film as \"a modern classic\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2008/05/02/52/Ar05200.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2008&DOCID=9635&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Anbe Sivam (Drama/Comedy) |last=Suganth |first=M. |date=2 May 2008 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105065738/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2008/05/02/52/Ar05200.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2008&DOCID=9635&Keyword=(%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam)&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=5 January 2017}}</ref> Reviewing the Telugu dubbed version, ''Sathyame Sivam'', Jeevi of [[Idlebrain.com]] said that \"this art-kind-of film does entertain the people who love Kamal Hassan flicks\" while concluding that it \"would remain as one of the good films made in the recent times\".<ref name=\"Jeevi\" />\n\nMalathi Rangarajan of ''The Hindu'' believed that \"well-defined characters, a strong storyline and intelligent screenplay\" were the film's \"vital ingredients\". She further complimented Haasan's treatment of the story, and that his \"diligence that has gone into the chiselling of the story and screenplay is only too evident\", while calling the film \"a laudable effort\".<ref name=\"MRReview\" /> P.{{nbsp}}Devarajan of ''[[Business Line]]'' appreciated Haasan's performance and facial expressions and concluded his review by stating, \"This man has intrigued me and will always.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2004/07/14/stories/2004071400272000.htm |title=The world of movies |last=Devarajan |first=P. |date=14 July 2004 |website=[[Business Line]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328061025/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2004/07/14/stories/2004071400272000.htm |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Another critic from ''The Hindu'', Gudipoodi Srihari, appreciated the pair of Haasan and Madhavan, noting that the duo \"make a fine combination of pals each with different mental make up, but goodness overflowing.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/03/04/stories/2003030400270400.htm |title=Worth watching |last=Srihari |first=Gudipoodi |date=4 March 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=12 June 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612091518/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/03/04/stories/2003030400270400.htm |archive-date=12 June 2016}}</ref> Sujatha Narayanan, in a retrospective review for ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' commended Haasan's writing and Madhan's dialogue, finding them to be \"peppered with sharp wit, trivia and emotional depth.\"<ref name=\"SNNIE\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/jan/08/films-for-life-1747249.html |title=Films for life |last=Narayanan |first=Sujatha |date=8 January 2018 |work=The New Indian Express |access-date=9 January 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109174010/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/jan/08/films-for-life-1747249.html |archive-date=9 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nA reviewer from [[Sify]], in comparison, labelled the film as \"average\", stating that it was \"another predictable and corny film which is neither a comedy caper nor a class act.\"<ref name=\"Sify Review\" /> Similarly, Arkay of Rediff.com praised the performances of the lead cast but wrote the film \"tries to do too many things, and ends up failing at most, if not all, of them.\"<ref name=\"Rediff Review\" /> S.{{nbsp}}Anand of ''Outlook'' felt the film's thematic ideas of communism were presented in a \"cliched\" manner, and summarised by saying, \"If Rajnikant staked claim to divinity on a right-wing plank with ''Baba'', Kamal does it with pretensions to rationalist-left rhetoric.\"<ref name=\"Outlook\" />\n\n=== Box office ===\nDuring the first week of its theatrical run, an analysis by [[Sudhish Kamath]] of ''The Hindu'' showed the film to have grossed {{INR}}13.1&nbsp;million in Chennai alone.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/lf/2003/01/22/stories/2003012200790200.htm |title=New maths for the box office |last=Kamath |first=Sudhish |date=22 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331154622/http://www.thehindu.com/lf/2003/01/22/stories/2003012200790200.htm |archive-date=31 March 2016 |author-link=Sudhish Kamath}}</ref>{{efn|name=exchange2003}} Despite this, the film [[Box office bomb|underperformed]] at the box office and incurred heavy losses for Lakshmi Movie Makers, effectively stopping them from investing in other ventures for the year 2003.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2003-08-26/news/27560133_1_tamil-film-ratnam-kavithalaya |title=Tamil films enter hit zone in 2003 |last=Govardan |first=D. |date=26 August 2003 |website=[[The Economic Times]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140308224817/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2003-08-26/news/27560133_1_tamil-film-ratnam-kavithalaya |archive-date=8 March 2014 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> An estimate by D.{{nbsp}}Govardan of ''[[The Economic Times]]'' places the losses at {{INR}}65&nbsp;million,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2003-04-22/news/27562298_1_kamal-hassan-rajkamal-films-international-sandiyar |title=Funds elude Kamal Hassan's mega flick |last=Govardan |first=D. |date=22 April 2003 |website=The Economic Times |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140308224811/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2003-04-22/news/27562298_1_kamal-hassan-rajkamal-films-international-sandiyar |archive-date=8 March 2014 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>{{efn|name=exchange2003}} while Arun Ram of ''[[India Today]]'' states the losses incurred to be {{INR}}50&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"bg\" /><ref name=\"fs\">{{Cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kollywood-producer-venkateswaran-suicide-raises-fears-of-box-office-losses-empty-theatres/1/206486.html |title=Flop show |last=Ram |first=Arun |date=19 May 2003 |work=India Today |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328124535/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kollywood-producer-venkateswaran-suicide-raises-fears-of-box-office-losses-empty-theatres/1/206486.html |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>{{efn|name=exchange2003}} Srinivasa Ramanujam of ''The Times of India'' compared the film's failure at the box office to that of ''Baba''.<ref name=\"Srinivasa Ramanujam 2008\" /> Both K. Muralitharan and Haasan defended the film's failure by blaming [[copyright infringement|video piracy]], with the latter stating that \"lots of people saw it, but they didn't pay\".<ref name=\"fs\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOIBG/2005/03/13/29/Ar02900.xml&CollName=TOI_BANGALORE_ARCHIVE&DOCID=285679&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=The Colour of My Cinema |last=Bala |first=Priya |date=13 March 2005 |website=The Times of India |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411072313/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOIBG%2F2005%2F03%2F13%2F29%2FAr02900.xml&CollName=TOI_BANGALORE_ARCHIVE&DOCID=285679&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=11 April 2016 |access-date=11 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"|Award\n! scope=\"col\"|Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"|Category\n! scope=\"col\"|Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\"|Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"sortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"4\" | [[Filmfare Awards South]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[51st Filmfare Awards South|12 June 2004]]\n| [[Filmfare Special Award&nbsp;\u2013 South|Special Jury Award]]\n| {{sort|Muralitharan|K. Muralitharan}}, V. Swaminathan, G. Venugopal\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" |<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/51st-Annual-Manikchand-Filmfare-Award-winners/articleshow/718496.cms |title=51st Annual Manikchand Filmfare Award winners |date=4 June 2004 |work=The Times of India |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150126140422/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/51st-Annual-Manikchand-Filmfare-Award-winners/articleshow/718496.cms |archive-date=26 January 2015}}</ref><br /><ref>{{Cite episode |title=51st Filmfare Awards South |series=Filmfare Awards |network=[[The Times Group]] |date=12 June 2004}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Film&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Film]]\n| {{sort|Muralitharan|K. Muralitharan}}, V. Swaminathan, G. Venugopal\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Actor]]\n| {{sort|Haasan|[[Kamal Haasan]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{sort|Madhavan|[[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\" | South Indian Cinematographers Association (SICA) Awards\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 23 November 2003\n| Best Actor\n| {{sort|Haasan|Kamal Haasan}}\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\" |<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/lf/2003/11/26/stories/2003112602720200.htm |title=Glamour, song, dance and stars |last=Lakshmi |first=K. |date=26 November 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328132448/http://www.thehindu.com/lf/2003/11/26/stories/2003112602720200.htm |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor\n| {{sort|Madhavan|[[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Art Director\n| {{sort|Prabhaharan|M. Prabhaharan}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\" | [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 30 September 2004\n| [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| {{sort|Madhavan|R.{{nbsp}}Madhavan}}<br /><small>(also for ''[[Kannathil Muthamittal]]'' and ''[[Run (2002 film)|Run]]'')</small>\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center; \"rowspan=\"2\" |<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/2004/10/01/stories/2004100112290500.htm |title=6 film artistes win top award |date=1 October 2004 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517093126/http://www.thehindu.com/2004/10/01/stories/2004100112290500.htm |archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Make-up Artist|Best Make-up Artist]]\n| {{sort|Rajan|V. P. Rajan}}\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n== Legacy ==\n{{Quote box\n |title =\n |quote = There's only one artiste in the whole Universe (!). It's Kamal Hassan. Without him there's no cinema. Have you watched ''Anbe Sivam''?\n |source =&nbsp;\u2013 Actor [[Nagesh]] in an interview with Malathi Rangarajan of ''The Hindu'' on whom he considered to be \"the best actor\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/behind-that-humorous-veneer/article2273149.ece |title=Behind that humorous veneer |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |date=27 July 2007 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328065205/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/behind-that-humorous-veneer/article2273149.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n |width  = 35%\n |align  = right\n}}\n\nFollowing its release, ''Anbe Sivam'' has attained [[cult film|cult status]] in Tamil cinema and receives re-runs on television channels.<ref name=\"SNNIE\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/happy-birthday-madhavan-6-roles-that-prove-he-has-an-amazing-acting-range-999699.html |title=Happy Birthday Madhavan: 6 roles that prove he has an amazing acting range |last=Rajpal |first=Roktim |date=1 July 2015 |website=[[CNN-News18]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105071022/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/happy-birthday-madhavan-6-roles-that-prove-he-has-an-amazing-acting-range-999699.html |archive-date=5 January 2017 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://indianexpress.com/photos/entertainment-gallery/happy-60th-birthday-kamal-haasan-top-roles/ |title=Happy 61st Birthday Kamal Haasan: The actor\u2019s top roles |date=7 November 2015 |work=The Indian Express |access-date=19 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105071355/http://indianexpress.com/photos/entertainment-gallery/happy-60th-birthday-kamal-haasan-top-roles/ |archive-date=5 January 2017 |page=13}}</ref> When the film was in post-production, Haasan revealed to film critic and journalist [[Subhash K. Jha]] that he was impressed with Madhavan's enthusiasm and performance during the making of the film, subsequently signing him to appear as the protagonist in his production venture, ''[[Nala Damayanthi (2003 film)|Nala Damayanthi]]'' (2003).<ref name=\"SKJRediff\" />\n\nBaradwaj Rangan wrote that ''Anbe Sivam'' was \"leagues ahead of the average Tamil{{snds}}why, even Indian{{snds}}film\", though he felt that \"the masses were unwilling to accept the experimental nature of the film\", while talking about the film's box office failure.<ref name=\"Rangan\" /> During his acceptance speech after winning the [[Vijay Award for Best Director]] in 2010 for ''[[Naan Kadavul]]'' (2009), director [[Bala (director)|Bala]] revealed that a scene in ''Anbe Sivam'' where Haasan says to Madhavan, \"when we love others unconditionally without any expectation, we become Gods\", inspired him to make his film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-inspired-me-bala-news-tamil-kkfq35ahjhg.html |title=''Anbe Sivam'' inspired me: Bala |last=Dhananjayan |first=G. |date=1 June 2010 |website=Sify |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328061453/http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-inspired-me-bala-news-tamil-kkfq35ahjhg.html |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Bala also made a reference to ''Anbe Sivam'' in his 2003 film, ''[[Pithamagan]]'', in a scene where [[Suriya]]'s character goes for a screening of the film with his friends.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2009/04/07/23/Ar02302.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=31318&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=The Times of India&nbsp;\u2013 Did You Know? |date=7 April 2009 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105065754/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2009/04/07/23/Ar02302.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=31318&Keyword=(%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam)&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=5 January 2017}}</ref> A dialogue told by Haasan to Madhavan, \"Do you know what a [[tsunami]] is? ''Periya alai illa{{nbsp}}... malai''.\" (It's not just a big wave{{nbsp}}... it's a mountain) also attained popularity.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/What-did-Kamal-Haasan-teach-us/article16439215.ece |title=What did Kamal Haasan teach us? |last=Ramanujam |first=Srinivasa |date=7 November 2016 |work=The Hindu |access-date=31 October 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105014954/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/What-did-Kamal-Haasan-teach-us/article16439215.ece |archive-date=5 January 2018 |last2=Menon |first2=Vishal}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, S.{{nbsp}}R. Ashok Kumar of ''The Hindu'' listed ''Anbe Sivam'' among the \"top five directorial ventures of Sundar{{nbsp}}C.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/heading-for-a-hat-trick/article1433672.ece |title=Heading for a hat trick? |last=Kumar |first=S. R. Ashok |date=28 March 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328065541/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/heading-for-a-hat-trick/article1433672.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> In a 2008 interview with ''The Times of India'', Sundar{{nbsp}}C. stated that ''Anbe Sivam'' \"changed [him] personally and professionally\", making him a more confident person and altering his outlook towards life.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/A-producers-delight/articleshow/3467611.cms |title=A producer's delight! |date=11 September 2008 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105070908/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/A-producers-delight/articleshow/3467611.cms |archive-date=5 January 2017}}</ref> He later contradicted his statement after revealing that the film's failure led him to become almost bankrupt and he remained unpaid for his work. The [[Income Tax Department]] froze his bank accounts for a year as he was not able to pay his taxes. He admitted that while he received praises for the film after its theatrical run, he would not make a film similar to ''Anbe Sivam'' anymore and that he chose to continue making commercial cinema, which he felt better matched his interests.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cinema.dinamalar.com/tamil-news/18919/cinema/Kollywood/I-lost-my-property-due-to-Anbe-Sivam-says-Sundar.C.htm |title=\u0b85\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc7 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0bb4\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0ba9\u0bcd \u2013 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf! |date=22 May 2014 |website=[[Dinamalar]] |language=Tamil |trans-title=I lost my property due to Anbe Sivam&nbsp;\u2013 An upset Sundar C! |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160714130237/http://cinema.dinamalar.com/tamil-news/18919/cinema/Kollywood/I-lost-my-property-due-to-Anbe-Sivam-says-Sundar.C.htm |archive-date=14 July 2016 |access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cinema.nakkheeran.in/Talkies.aspx?T=2085 |title=\"\u0b85\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc7 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bbf \u0b87\u0baf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc7\u0ba9\u0bcd\"&nbsp;\u2013 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bcd.\u0b9a\u0bbf! |date=13 March 2013 |website=[[Nakkheeran]] |language=Tamil |trans-title=\"I will not direct films like Anbe Sivam anymore\"&nbsp;\u2013 Sundar C! |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130316033755/http://cinema.nakkheeran.in/Talkies.aspx?T=2085 |archive-date=16 March 2013 |access-date=13 April 2016}}</ref> In 2013, Haricharan Pudipeddi of the [[Indo-Asian News Service]] agency, included ''Anbe Sivam'' in his list of \"Kamal's most underrated films\". He believed the reason for the film's commercial failure was that audiences misunderstood the \"sarcastic undertones associated with atheism\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/on-his-59th-b-day-kamal-haasan-s-most-underrated-films-news-national-nlhk4gceibgsi.html |title=On his 59th b'day, Kamal Haasan's most underrated films |last=Pudipeddi |first=Haricharan |date=7 November 2013 |access-date=27 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327132456/http://www.sify.com/movies/on-his-59th-b-day-kamal-haasan-s-most-underrated-films-news-national-nlhk4gceibgsi.html |archive-date=27 March 2016 |agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service]] |website=Sify}}</ref> On Haasan's birthday, 7 November 2015, Latha Srinivasan of ''[[Daily News and Analysis]]'' considered ''Anbe Sivam'' to be one of the \"films you must watch to grasp the breadth of Kamal Haasan's repertoire\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-birthday-special-films-you-must-watch-to-grasp-the-breadth-of-kamal-haasan-s-repertoire-2143008 |title=Birthday special: Films you must watch to grasp the breadth of Kamal Haasan's repertoire |last=Srinivasan |first=Latha |date=7 November 2015 |work=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6gL5edduL?url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-birthday-special-films-you-must-watch-to-grasp-the-breadth-of-kamal-haasan-s-repertoire-2143008 |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> The character of Nallasivam was ranked fourth in ''The Times of India'''s list of \"Kamal Haasan's top 10 mind-blowing avatars\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/Kamal-Haasans-top-10-mind-blowing-avatars/photostory/45058497.cms |title=Kamal Haasan's top 10 mind-blowing avatars |website=The Times of India |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105071003/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/Kamal-Haasans-top-10-mind-blowing-avatars/photostory/45058497.cms |archive-date=5 January 2017 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn ''[[Vasool Raja MBBS]]'' (2004), the character Vasool Raja (Haasan), while attending a class asks whether being a doctor is equivalent to being God, and in doing so says \"Anbe Venkatachalam\", to which one of his classmates gently asks him, \"isn't it Anbe Sivam?\". Haasan retorts: \"Let it be. Let's try something different for a change.\"<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QjTlT4VEiLc |title=Vasool Raja MBBS Tamil Movie&nbsp;\u2013 Kamal, Sneha, Prabhu, Prakash Raj |last=Kamal Haasan, Sneha, Prabhu Ganesan, Prakash Raj |year=2004 |place=India |access-date=8 January 2018 |website=[[YouTube]] |medium=motion picture}}</ref> The street theatre sequence featuring Kamal's character, Nallasivam, and his friends performing to make people aware of the atrocities committed by Nassar's character, Kanadasamy Padayatchi, was re-created at [[Tiruchirappalli]] in 2008 by Pralayan and his troupe from \"Chennai Kalai Kuzhu\" under the title ''Nammal Mudiyum''. In contrast, Pralayan's play explored gender inequality and domestic violence instead of unemployment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/a-street-play-in-a-theatre-ambience/article1234535.ece |title=A street play in a theatre ambience |last=Aishwarya |first=S. |date=7 April 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328074452/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/a-street-play-in-a-theatre-ambience/article1234535.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Kannada actor [[Vishnuvardhan (actor)|Vishnuvardhan]] noted in 2010 that fellow actor [[Sudeep]]'s film ''[[Just Maath Maathalli]]'' (2010) bears resemblance to ''Anbe Sivam''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/its-more-than-mere-banter/article789113.ece |title=It's more than mere banter |last=Kumar |first=S. Shiva |date=12 February 2010 |website=The Hindu |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328072117/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/its-more-than-mere-banter/article789113.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Hari Narayan, writing for ''The Hindu'' in 2014, mentions in his article on the Indian [[Rationalism|rationalist]] and author [[Narendra Dabholkar]] that [[Umesh Shukla]]'s ''[[OMG&nbsp;\u2013 Oh My God!]]'' (2012) was \"a toned down version of ''Anbe Sivam'' where rationality propels humans to find God in themselves, with flaws, which extols the virtue of becoming as much as that of being\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/blogs/blog-by-the-way/article5635194.ece |title=Fulcrum for the faithless souls |last=Narayan |first=Hari |date=31 January 2014 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328073613/http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/blogs/blog-by-the-way/article5635194.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> In 2015 Uthiran of ''[[The Hindu (Tamil)|The Hindu]]'' in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], mentions in his review of ''[[Orange Mittai]]'' (2015) that the film's plot \"might remind viewers of ''Anbe Sivam''\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://tamil.thehindu.com/cinema/tamil-cinema/%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%A4%E0%AE%B2%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%AA%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%B0%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%B5%E0%AF%88-%E0%AE%86%E0%AE%B0%E0%AE%9E%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9A%E0%AF%81-%E0%AE%AE%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%9F%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9F%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%AF%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%87%E0%AE%A9%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%B3%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%8D/article7486062.ece |title=\u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc8: \u0b86\u0bb0\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bcd&nbsp;\u2013 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd |last=\u0b89\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd |date=31 July 2015 |work=[[The Hindu (Tamil)|The Hindu]] |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328093400/http://tamil.thehindu.com/cinema/tamil-cinema/%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%A4%E0%AE%B2%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%AA%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%B0%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%B5%E0%AF%88-%E0%AE%86%E0%AE%B0%E0%AE%9E%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9A%E0%AF%81-%E0%AE%AE%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%9F%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9F%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%AF%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%87%E0%AE%A9%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%B3%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%8D/article7486062.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016 |language=Tamil |trans-title=First Look: Orange Mittai&nbsp;\u2014 The pros and cons}}</ref> In 2017, Ashok, who directed the comedy film ''[[Peechankai]]'', mentions he was inspired by ''Anbe Sivam'' to become a director.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/director-of-peechaankai-ashok-talks-about-his-film/article19055414.ece |title=Director Ashok talks about his first feature, the quirky 'Peechaankai' |last=J. Rao |first=Subha |date=15 June 2017 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 June 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617083107/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/director-of-peechaankai-ashok-talks-about-his-film/article19055414.ece |archive-date=17 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/peechankai-review-the-left-comes-to-power/article19087971.ece |title='Peechankai': the left comes to power |last=Ramanujam |first=Srinivasa |date=16 June 2017 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 June 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617083112/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/peechankai-review-the-left-comes-to-power/article19087971.ece |archive-date=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== Film ==\n* {{cite AV media | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qFA7REldr88 | title=Anbe Sivam Tamil Full Movie&nbsp;\u2013 Kamal Haasan, Madhavan, Kiran | publisher=[[Pyramid Saimira|Pyramid Movies]] | date=30 May 2014 | accessdate=26 March 2016 | people=Kamal Haasan, R.{{nbsp}}Madhavan, Kiran Rathod, Nassar | medium=Motion Picture | location=India | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160523072756/https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qFA7REldr88 | archivedate=23 May 2016 | url-status=live | ref={{Sfnref|Pyramid Movies|2014}}}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0367495|title=Anbe Sivam}}\n* {{Rotten-tomatoes|anbe_sivam|Anbe Sivam}}\n\n{{Kamal Haasan}}\n{{Sundar C.}}\n\n[[Category:2000s Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2000s comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:2003 films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Sundar C.]]\n[[Category:Films set in Andhra Pradesh]]\n[[Category:Films set in Odisha]]\n[[Category:Indian avant-garde and experimental films]]\n[[Category:Indian comedy-drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian road movies]]\n[[Category:Indian nonlinear narrative films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Kamal Haasan]]\n[[Category:Tamil films scored by Vidyasagar]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language films]]\n[[Category:2000s avant-garde and experimental films]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2003 film by Sundar C.}}\n{{featured article}}\n{{EngvarB|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Anbe Sivam\n| image          = Anbe Sivam.jpg\n| alt            = Poster featuring Kamal Haasan (\"left\") and {{nbsp}}Madhavan (\"right\")\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Sundar C.]]\n| producer       = {{plainlist|\n* K. Muralitharan\n* V. Swaminathan\n* G. Venugopal\n* Sundar C.\n}}\n| writer         = {{plainlist|\n* [[Kamal Haasan]]\n}}\n| starring       = {{plainlist|\n* Kamal Haasan\n* [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]\n* [[Kiran Rathod]]\n}}\n| music          = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cinematography = [[Arthur A. Wilson]]\n| editing        = [[P. Sai Suresh]]\n| studio         = [[Lakshmi Movie Makers]]\n| distributor    = Lakshmi Movie Makers\n| released       = {{Film date|2003|01|15|df=y}}<ref name=\"ASBBFC\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/anbea-sivam-1970 |title=Anbea Sivam (12A) |website=[[British Board of Film Classification]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517052505/http://www.bbfc.co.uk/releases/anbea-sivam-1970 |archive-date=17 May 2016 |access-date=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n| runtime        = 160 minutes<ref name=\"Panorama\">{{Cite web |url=http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/FrmIP2003Award.aspx?PdfName=IP2003.pdf |title=2003 Indian Panorama |publisher=[[Directorate of Film Festivals]] |format=PDF |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328100714/http://iffi.nic.in/Dff2011/FrmIP2003Award.aspx?PdfName=IP2003.pdf |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n| country        = India\n| language       = Tamil\n| budget         = [[Indian rupee sign|{{INR}}]]120&nbsp;million<ref name=\"bg\">{{Cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/with-chandramukhi-tamil-superstar-rajnikant-revives-his-fading-career/1/193427.html |title=Return of the king |last=Ram |first=Arun |date=20 June 2005 |work=[[India Today]] |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140925135648/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/with-chandramukhi-tamil-superstar-rajnikant-revives-his-fading-career/1/193427.html |archive-date=25 September 2014}}</ref>{{efn|The average exchange rate in 2003 was 45.66 [[Indian rupee]]s ({{INR}}) per 1 US dollar (US$).<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://inwww.rediff.com/business/slide-show/slide-show-1-rupee-vs-dollar-in-the-last-2-decades/20120518.htm?print=true |title=Rupee vs dollar: From 1990 to 2012 |date=18 May 2012 |website=[[Rediff.com]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150321115240/http://inwww.rediff.com/business/slide-show/slide-show-1-rupee-vs-dollar-in-the-last-2-decades/20120518.htm?print=true |archive-date=21 March 2015 |access-date=31 March 2016}}</ref>|name=exchange2003}}\n}}\n\n'''''Anbe Sivam''''' ({{trans|Love is God}})<ref name=\"Swarajya1\">{{Cite web |url=https://swarajyamag.com/culture/anbe-sivam-misleading-title-that-matches-the-purpose |title=Anbe Sivam: Stairway To The Pseudo-Secular Heaven |last=Neelakandan |first=Aravindan |date=5 May 2017 |website=[[Swarajya (magazine)|Swarajya]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109154017/https://swarajyamag.com/culture/anbe-sivam-misleading-title-that-matches-the-purpose |archive-date=9 January 2018 |access-date=9 January 2018}}</ref> is a 2003 Indian [[Tamil language|Tamil]]-language [[comedy-drama]] film directed and co-produced by [[Sundar C.]] with K. Muralitharan, V. Swaminathan and G. Venugopal under the banner of [[Lakshmi Movie Makers]]. The film was written by [[Kamal Haasan]], and [[Madhan (writer)|Madhan]] provided the dialogues. ''Anbe Sivam'' features Haasan, [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]] and [[Kiran Rathod]] in the lead roles, with [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]], [[Santhana Bharathi]], [[Seema (actress)|Seema]] and [[Uma Riyaz Khan]] playing supporting characters.\n\nThe film tells the story of an unexpected journey from [[Bhubaneswar]] to [[Chennai]] undertaken by two men of contrasting personalities, Nallasivam and Anbarasu. The musical score was composed by [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]. [[Arthur A. Wilson]] and M. Prabhaharan undertook responsibility for the film's cinematography and art direction, respectively.\n\nProduced on a budget of [[Indian rupee sign|{{INR}}]]120&nbsp;million, ''Anbe Sivam'' takes on several themes, including [[communism]], [[atheism]], and [[altruism]], and depicts Haasan's views as a [[Humanism|humanist]]. The film was released on 15 January 2003 to positive reviews from critics, but [[Box-office bomb|underperformed]] at the box office. Despite its failure, it gained recognition over the years through re-runs on television channels and is now regarded as a classic and a [[cult film]] in [[Tamil cinema]].\n\n''Anbe Sivam'' was screened as part of the Indian Panorama section of the [[International Film Festival of India]] in 2003. At the [[51st Filmfare Awards South]], it received a [[Filmfare Special Award&nbsp;\u2013 South|Special Jury Award]] and received nominations in the [[Filmfare Award for Best Film&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Film]] and [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Actor]] (Haasan) categories. Madhavan was awarded [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]] at the 2003 [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]].\n\n== Plot ==\nTwo men waiting for a flight to [[Chennai]] at the [[Biju Patnaik International Airport]] in [[Bhubaneswar]] engage in conversation. One is a [[commercial director]], Anbarasu, who prefers the abbreviated name A.{{nbsp}}Aras, and the other is a scarred and deformed socialist, Nallasivam, alias Nalla. When the flight is cancelled due to heavy rain, Aras initially suspects Nalla is a terrorist and informs the authorities, only to discover that he was mistaken. With the rain flooding the city, the two men are forced to share a room for the night. Both need to return to Chennai: Aras to be present at his wedding, and Nalla has to deliver a {{INR}}3,200,000{{efn|name=exchange2003}} cheque, recently awarded to him after he won a court case, to a group of union workers. After a traumatic night, and no hope for a flight, the two men take a bus to board the [[Coromandel Express]] train. Aras' bag gets stolen on the way leaving him with only his credit card, which no one accepts. Using his presence of mind, Nalla repeatedly bails Aras out of trouble while Aras tries escaping from him at every juncture, only to end up with him again. While waiting for the train at the [[Ichchapuram]] railway station, Nalla begins to tell Aras his story.\n\nA few years earlier, a healthy Nalla took part in various [[street theatre]] performances protesting against [[Foreign direct investment|multinational corporation-driven industrialisation]], that resulted in the marginalisation of the [[Workforce|labour force]]. He was at odds with Kandasamy Padayatchi, a manipulative factory owner who refused to give his workers a raise. Nalla satirically imitated Padayatchi in many of his shows. However, in an unexpected turn of events, Nalla and Padayatchi's daughter Balasaraswathi alias Bala, fell in love with each other. To avoid a potential conflict with Padayatchi, the two decided to elope to Kerala. Nalla boarded a bus bound for Kerala, and on his way to meet Bala, the bus crashed on a hillside leaving him scarred, disfigured, and partially paralysed for life. After recovering from his wounds, he visited Bala only to be informed by Padayatchi that his daughter was already married and has settled abroad. Padayatchi had earlier lied to Bala that Nalla died in the accident. It was also at this time that Nalla became a firm believer in kindness and love. Despite suffering from an inferiority complex due to his scarred and deformed body, Nalla performs community service and social work with renewed fervour while continuing to fight for union causes.\n\nUpon their arrival at Chennai, Aras delivers Nalla's cheque to the union workers. He invites Nalla to his wedding, where, to his utter astonishment, Nalla sees that Aras's bride is Bala. Padayatchi spots Nalla and asks him why he is at the wedding. He tells Padayatchi that he was invited by Aras, and later persuades him to sign the papers which will help Padayatchi's workers get a raise. To prevent the disruption of Bala's wedding and avoid damaging his own reputation, Padayatchi yields to Nalla's demands. After signing the papers, Padayatchi instructs his assistant to eliminate Nalla. However, his assistant has a change of heart as he is about to kill him. Padayatchi's assistant believes that the misdeeds he committed for Padayatchi resulted in the death of the assistant's daughter. Padayatchi's assistant requests Nalla to stay as far away from his boss as possible; Nalla assents and walks away.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{multiple image\n| direction = horizontal\n| width1    = 209\n| width2    = 200\n| footer    = [[Kamal Haasan]] and [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]] play the roles of Nallasivam and Anbarasu, respectively.\n| image1    = Kamal Haasan at 62nd Filmfare Awards south.jpg\n| alt1      = Kamal Haasan posing for the camera at the 62nd Filmfare Awards South ceremony\n| image2    = Madhavan Saala Khadoos (cropped).jpg\n| alt2      = Madhavan posing for the camera at the premiere of his 2016 film Saala Khadoos\n}}\n* [[Kamal Haasan]] as Nallasivam alias Nalla{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]] as Anbarasu alias A. Aras{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Kiran Rathod]] as Balasaraswathi alias Bala{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Nassar (actor)|Nassar]] as Kandasamy Padayatchi{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Santhana Bharathi]] as Padayatchi's assistant{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Seema (actress)|Seema]] as Balasaraswathi's aunt{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}\n* [[Yugi Sethu]] as Uthaman<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2010/02/05/26/Ar02600.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=147160&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Content is king |last=Pillai |first=Sreedhar |date=5 February 2010 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410134013/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH%2F2010%2F02%2F05%2F26%2FAr02600.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=147160&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=10 April 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Uma Riyaz Khan]] as Mehrunissa{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 53:18 to 53:25}}<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/260417/not-just-a-star-wife-uma.html |title=Not just a star wife: Uma |last=Nair |first=Vidya |date=26 April 2017 |work=[[Deccan Chronicle]] |access-date=30 April 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170430160205/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/260417/not-just-a-star-wife-uma.html |archive-date=30 April 2017}}</ref>\n* [[Pasi Sathya]] as a tea stall owner<ref name=\"MRReview\" />\n* Sujatha Narayanan as a tea shop owner who helps Nallasivam<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/Expert-Juggler-of-Trades-Revels-in-Her-Bliss/2016/03/24/article3342669.ece |title=Expert Juggler of Trades Revels in Her Bliss |last=Chandni |first=U. |date=24 March 2016 |work=[[The New Indian Express]] |access-date=31 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331080817/http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/Expert-Juggler-of-Trades-Revels-in-Her-Bliss/2016/03/24/article3342669.ece |archive-date=31 March 2016}}</ref>{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:44:05 to 1:46:25}} \n* [[Balu Anand]] as the train ticket checker for the Coromandel Express<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/actor-balu-anand-passes-away/article8686086.ece |title=Actor Balu Anand passes away |date=3 June 2016 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=6 June 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606145950/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/actor-balu-anand-passes-away/article8686086.ece |archive-date=6 June 2016}}</ref>{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:54:25 to 1:55:40}}\n* [[R. S. Shivaji]] as the Ichchapuram railway station master<ref name=\"MRReview\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:54:25 to 1:55:40}}\n* [[Ilavarasu]] as a police inspector and aide of Padayatchi<ref name=\"MRReview\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:17:22 to 1:19:34}}\n\n== Production ==\n=== Development ===\nAfter completing the draft for a film's script in early 2002, Kamal Haasan approached the [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] filmmaker [[Priyadarshan]] to direct it.<ref name=\"SWP\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/24priyan.htm |title=No regrets, no remakes |last=Warrier |first=Shobha |date=24 April 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325133257/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/24priyan.htm |archive-date=25 March 2016 |access-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> The two men were keen to work together since the late 1990s, and upon reading the script, Priyadarshan believed that it had the potential to be an \"emotional love story\".<ref name=\"SWP\" /> The film's title ''Anbe Sivam'' was derived from the [[Shaivism|Shaivite]] saint [[Tirumular]]'s poem ''[[Tirumantiram]]''.<ref name=\"SRAKMR\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/03/29/stories/2002032901230300.htm |title=The long and short of it... |last=Kumar |first=S. R. Ashok |date=29 March 2002 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326092025/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/03/29/stories/2002032901230300.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |last2=Rangarajan |first2=Malathi}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2002, Priyadarshan opted out of the project owing to creative differences.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/jun/14priyan.htm |title=Priyadarshan out of Kamal's film |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |authorlink=Subhash K. Jha |date=14 June 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325143149/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/jun/14priyan.htm |archive-date=25 March 2016 |access-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> He was replaced by [[Sundar C.]], who agreed to produce the film as well.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/its-all-fun-and-frolic/article3387502.ece |title=It's all fun and frolic |last=Manigandan |first=K. R. |date=5 May 2012 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328075229/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/its-all-fun-and-frolic/article3387502.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> ''Anbe Sivam'' was co-produced and distributed by Swaminathan, K.{{nbsp}}Muralitharan and G.{{nbsp}}Venugopal under the production banner of [[Lakshmi Movie Makers]].{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}<ref name=\"BH\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/64853/Anbe%20Sivam |title=Anbe Sivam |website=[[Bollywood Hungama]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517023623/http://www.bollywoodhungama.com/moviemicro/cast/id/64853/Anbe%20Sivam |archive-date=17 May 2016 |access-date=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Cast and crew ===\nIn addition to being the film's writer, Haasan also played the central character. Madhavan was selected to play the film's second lead in January 2002.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/jan/19kamal.htm |title=Kamal, Madhavan: Boys just wanna have fun |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=19 January 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325142732/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/jan/19kamal.htm |archive-date=25 March 2016 |access-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> According to Kiran Rathod, she received a phone call from Haasan's office informing her that she was offered the role of Balasaraswathi, which she accepted.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/how-i-met-kamal-haasan/article6570994.ece |title=How I met Kamal Haasan |last=Ramanujam |first=Srinivasa |date=6 November 2014 |work=The Hindu |access-date=25 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325141010/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/how-i-met-kamal-haasan/article6570994.ece |archive-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> Rathod's voice in the film was dubbed by the singer [[Anuradha Sriram]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Repository/getFiles.asp?Style=OliveXLib:LowLevelEntityToPrintGifMSIE_PASTISSUES2&Type=text/html&Locale=english-skin-custom&Path=TOICH/2011/04/23&ChunkNum=0&ID=Ar03005 |title=Did You Know? |date=23 April 2011 |work=The Times of India |access-date=8 January 2018 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180108102952/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Repository/getFiles.asp?Style=OliveXLib%3ALowLevelEntityToPrintGifMSIE_PASTISSUES2&Type=text%2Fhtml&Locale=english-skin-custom&Path=TOICH%2F2011%2F04%2F23&ChunkNum=0&ID=Ar03005 |archive-date=8 January 2018 |location=Chennai |page=30}}</ref> Uma Riyaz Khan played the role of Kamal's friend and professional colleague, Mehrunissa.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://archives.deccanchronicle.com/130530/entertainment-kollywood/article/mommy-rocks |title=This mommy rocks! |last=Das |first=Papri |date=30 May 2013 |work=Deccan Chronicle |access-date=25 March 2016 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150619114816/http://archives.deccanchronicle.com/130530/entertainment-kollywood/article/mommy-rocks |archive-date=19 June 2015}}</ref> In a 2019 interview with ''[[The Indian Express]]'', the film's script assistant and costume designer, Sujatha Narayanan, revealed that [[Nandita Das]] and [[Shobana]] were the original choices for Balasaraswathi and Mehrunissa respectively and that both of them declined due to schedule conflicts.<ref name=\"AS16\">{{Cite news |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/what-makes-kamal-haasan-anbe-sivam-a-timeless-classic-5540160/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/what-makes-kamal-haasan-anbe-sivam-a-timeless-classic-5540160/ |title=What makes Kamal Haasan\u2019s Anbe Sivam a timeless classic |last=Subhakeerthana |first=S. |date=15 January 2019 |work=[[The Indian Express]] |access-date=29 March 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190329053429/https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/tamil/what-makes-kamal-haasan-anbe-sivam-a-timeless-classic-5540160/ |archive-date=29 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n{{Quote|text = He [Kamal] came over to me and said, 'Madhavan, I have seen some of your work and they were good.' [...] Then he continued, 'I have something for you. We should catch up!' [...] that was how ''Anbe Sivam'' happened.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/may/30maddy.htm |title=After Anbe Sivam, I became a hardcore Kamal fan |last=Warrier |first=Shobha |date=30 May 2008 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326021810/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2008/may/30maddy.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=26 March 2016}}</ref>|author = Madhavan on how he was cast in ''Anbe Sivam''|width = 35%|align = right}}\n\nThe actors Nassar and Santhana Bharathi played the roles of Kandasamy Padaiyatchi and his assistant, respectively, while cartoonist [[Madhan (writer)|Madhan]] featured in a cameo appearance as himself in addition to writing the film's dialogues.<ref name=\"BH\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 50:35 to 56:45}} In an interview with S.{{nbsp}}R. Ashok Kumar of ''[[The Hindu]]'' in 2006, Bharathi considered both ''Anbe Sivam'' and ''[[Michael Madana Kama Rajan]]'' (1990) to be the favourite roles of his career.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/this-character-artists-first-love-is-direction/article3048491.ece |title=This character artist's first love is direction |last=Kumar |first=S. R. Ashok |date=16 November 2006 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328064501/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/this-character-artists-first-love-is-direction/article3048491.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[Arthur A. Wilson]], [[M. Prabhaharan]] and [[P. Sai Suresh]] handled the film's cinematography, art direction and editing, respectively.{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Opening credits from 01:25 to 03:05}}<ref name=\"MRReview\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701310200.htm |title=Anbe Sivam |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |date=17 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326075815/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701310200.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref> [[Brinda (choreographer)|Brinda]], [[Chinni Prakash]] and [[Dinesh Kumar (choreographer)|Dinesh Kumar]] were in charge of the choreography while the stunt sequences were co-ordinated by [[Vikram Dharma]].<ref name=\"SRAK\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/10/stories/2003011001100200.htm |title=Films add glamour to harvest festival |last=Kumar |first=S. R. Ashok |date=10 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326081244/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/10/stories/2003011001100200.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.cinemaexpress.com/cinemaexpress/story.aspx?Title=%E0%AE%86%E0%AE%9F%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9F+%E0%AE%A8%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%AF%E0%AE%95%E0%AE%A9%E0%AF%8D!&artid=112043&SectionID=144&MainSectionID=144&SectionName=Fashion&SEO= |title=\u0b86\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd! |last=\u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bcd |first=\u0b95\u0bbe\u0bb5\u0bc7\u0bb0\u0bbf |website=[[Cinema Express]] |language=Tamil |trans-title=King of Dance! |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20160909091120/http://web.archive.org/web/20160328094215/http://www.cinemaexpress.com/cinemaexpress/story.aspx?Title=%E0%AE%86%E0%AE%9F\u0bcd\u0b9f+\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0ba9\u0bcd!&artid=112043&SectionID=144&MainSectionID=144&SectionName=Fashion&SEO= |archive-date=9 September 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Muthulakshmi Varadhan, Bharathi's sister-in-law, worked as an assistant editor in the film.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2012/03/08/26/Ar02600.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=451459&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Meet The Path-Breakers |last=Suresh |first=Sunayana |date=8 March 2012 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410081243/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH%2F2012%2F03%2F08%2F26%2FAr02600.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=451459&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=10 April 2016 |last2=Ramanujam |first2=Srinivasa |last3=Bharathan |first3=Bijoy |last4=Lakshmi |first4=V. |last5=Panikker |first5=Rohit |last6=Abudul Kareem |first6=Rehan}}</ref> The make-up for Haasan's scars was designed by [[Michael Westmore]] and Anil Premkarikar.<ref name=\"SRAK\" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/10/15/stories/2004101502460500.htm |title=From Texas to tinsel town |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |date=15 October 2004 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328085847/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2004/10/15/stories/2004101502460500.htm |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> In May 2002, Haasan completed the makeup for his character Nallasivam in Los Angeles after filming the song sequences for ''[[Panchathantiram]]'' (2002).<ref name=\"SRAKMR\" /><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/05/03/stories/2002050300320300.htm |title=Harrowing time in Toronto |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=3 May 2002 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326092734/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2002/05/03/stories/2002050300320300.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/30kamal.htm |title=What it means to be Kamal Haasan |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=30 April 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326093732/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/apr/30kamal.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=26 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n=== Filming ===\n[[Principal photography]] for ''Anbe Sivam'' commenced in July 2002.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/jul/16kamal.htm |title='I'm working to clear debts' |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=16 July 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160325143520/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/jul/16kamal.htm |archive-date=25 March 2016 |access-date=25 March 2016}}</ref> The first scene featuring the lead actors was shot at [[Pollachi Junction railway station]]. Haasan and Madhavan interacted closely during the initial stages of the shoot to ensure that the on-screen chemistry between the pair was apparent.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/sep/23kamal.htm |title=Facing the camera with The Legend |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=23 September 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326014654/http://www.rediff.com/entertai/2002/sep/23kamal.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=26 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n''Anbe Sivam'' was shot on a restricted budget of {{INR}}120&nbsp;million, with the train and bus disaster sequences involving the use of settings and [[Computer-generated imagery|CGI]].<ref name=\"bg\" />{{efn|name=exchange2003}} Madhavan, who began shooting his portions in September 2002,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/sep/20mad.htm |title='It's an out-and-out Madhavan film!' |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=20 September 2002 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170106105356/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2002/sep/20mad.htm |archive-date=6 January 2017 |access-date=6 January 2017}}</ref> stated the film was shot in relatively empty locations.<ref name=\"SKJRediff\">{{Cite web |url=http://in.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/09kamal.htm |title=Kamal Haasan and Madhavan on their film Anbesivam |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=9 January 2003 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326014635/http://in.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/09kamal.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=11 June 2013}}</ref> The flood scenes set in [[Odisha]] were re-created with outdoor sets consisting of city roads submerged under water erected in the Odisha-[[Andhra Pradesh]] border.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOIM/2005/03/29/36/Ar03600.xml&CollName=TOI_MUMBAI_ARCHIVE&DOCID=434728&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Tsunami Premonitions |date=29 March 2005 |work=The Times of India |access-date=11 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411073938/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOIM%2F2005%2F03%2F29%2F36%2FAr03600.xml&CollName=TOI_MUMBAI_ARCHIVE&DOCID=434728&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=11 April 2016}}</ref> Filming also took place in Chennai, [[Visakhapatnam]] and on the [[Tamil Nadu]]-[[Karnataka]] border.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/01/14/stories/2003011400390400.htm |title=Madhavan makes his move |last=Rajamani |first=Radhika |date=14 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326014557/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/01/14/stories/2003011400390400.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref> The pre-climax scenes were filmed in what was then known as the [[Campa Cola]] compound in Guindy.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2016/nov/06/what-you-learn-just-by-watching-kamal-haasan-1535684.html |title=What you learn just by watching Kamal Haasan |last=Narayanan |first=Sujatha |date=6 November 2016 |website=The New Indian Express |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161108142018/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2016/nov/06/what-you-learn-just-by-watching-kamal-haasan-1535684.html |archive-date=8 November 2016 |access-date=8 November 2016}}</ref> The climax scenes were filmed in a single take.<ref name=\"AS16\" />\n\n== Themes and influences ==\n''Anbe Sivam'' follows the events of a journey from Bhubaneswar to Chennai undertaken by two men of contrasting personalities, Nallasivam (Haasan), a physically challenged and witty socialist, and Anbarasu (Madhavan), a commercial director who supports [[capitalism]] and [[Globalization|globalisation]].<ref name=\"Pujaafive\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/my-five-r-pujaa/article5609403.ece |title=My five |last=Pujaa |first=R. |date=23 January 2014 |website=The Hindu |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326143212/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/my-five-r-pujaa/article5609403.ece |archive-date=26 March 2016 |access-date=26 March 2016}}</ref> Due to unforeseen circumstances, the two are forced to undertake the journey together.<ref name=\"Sify Review\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-review-tamil-12525931.html |title=Anbe Sivam |website=[[Sify]] |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140411181523/http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-review-tamil-12525931.html |archive-date=11 April 2014 |access-date=27 March 2016}}</ref> Throughout the narrative, a series of themes pertaining to [[communism]],{{efn|Nalla and Aras argue about the topics at the Ichchapuram railway station.{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:46:40 to 1:50:40}}|name=Topic}} compassion, globalisation,{{efn|name=Topic}} [[atheism]], and [[altruism]]{{efn|Aras donates blood to save a boy injured in a train accident from dying.{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 2:02:00 to 2:11:00}}}} are addressed; the film also showcases Haasan's views as a [[Humanism|humanist]].<ref name=\"Swarajya1\" /><ref name=\"Pujaafive\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.ibtimes.co.in/after-039ninaithale-inikkum039-kamal039s-039anbe-sivam039-may-get-a-re-release-507926 |title=After 'Ninaithale Inikkum', Haasan's 'Anbe Sivam' May Get a Re-Release |date=22 September 2013 |website=[[International Business Times]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327135713/http://www.ibtimes.co.in/after-039ninaithale-inikkum039-kamal039s-039anbe-sivam039-may-get-a-re-release-507926 |archive-date=27 March 2016 |access-date=27 March 2016}}</ref> According to Haasan, the characterisation of Nallasivam was inspired by the life of Communist playwright, actor, director, lyricist and theorist [[Safdar Hashmi]], who was chiefly associated with his work on [[street theatre]] in India.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2003/01/14/stories/2003011400910200.htm |title=No branding please... |last=Nayar |first=Mandira |date=14 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517020841/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/lf/2003/01/14/stories/2003011400910200.htm |archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref> Hashmi died on 2 January 1989 after being attacked by members of the [[Indian National Congress]] while staging a play, ''Halla Bol''.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/drX89IpmCMTnyZpu5mowmM/Halla-Bol--Of-the-people-by-the-people.html |title=Halla Bol: Of the people, by the people |last=Ghosh |first=Tanushree |date=24 February 2014 |work=[[Mint (newspaper)|Mint]] |access-date=17 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517021134/http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/drX89IpmCMTnyZpu5mowmM/Halla-Bol--Of-the-people-by-the-people.html |archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref> S.{{nbsp}}Anand of ''[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]]'' magazine notes that Haasan's views on humanism in the film also seemed to be inspired by those of [[Charlie Chaplin]].<ref name=\"Outlook\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/anbey-sivam-love-is-god/218710 |title=Anbey Sivam (Love is God) |last=Anand |first=S. |date=27 January 2003 |website=[[Outlook (Indian magazine)|Outlook]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327131901/http://www.outlookindia.com/magazine/story/anbey-sivam-love-is-god/218710 |archive-date=27 March 2016 |access-date=27 March 2016}}</ref> M. Kalyanaraman and Abdullah Nurullah of ''[[The Times of India]]'' opined that Nallasivam shared similar characteristics with street theatre artist Pralayan.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Is-Kamal-trending-lotus/articleshow/49824678.cms |title=Is Kamal trending lotus? |last=Kalyanaraman & Abdullah Nurullah |first=M. |date=18 November 2015 |work=The Times of India |access-date=6 June 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160606135513/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/Is-Kamal-trending-lotus/articleshow/49824678.cms |archive-date=6 June 2016 |last2=Nurullah |first2=Abdullah}}</ref>\n\nAccording to Kalyanaraman, ''Anbe Sivam'' proposes that man can make morally superior choices when he comes face to face with death. As a result, Haasan indicates that the belief of \"[[Shiva|Siva]] is love\" is the \"final stage of evolution of man into God\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/The-spiritual-Kamal-Hassan/articleshow/47204923.cms |title=The spiritual Kamal Hassan |last=Kalyanaraman |first=M. |date=8 May 2015 |website=The Times of India |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20161127164445/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/chennai/The-spiritual-Kamal-Hassan/articleshow/47204923.cms |archive-date=27 November 2016 |access-date=10 April 2016}}</ref> The film features a Tamil proverb from [[Manikkavacakar]]'s ''[[Tiruvacakam]]'', ''Tenn\u0101\u1e6du\u1e6daiya \u015aivan\u0113 p\u00f6\u1e5b\u1e5bi'' (\"Praise \u015aiva who resides in the ancient land and who belongs to all of humanity\"). Padayatchi utters this every time before he murders or assaults a person. Kalavai Venkat of ''[[Swarajya (magazine)|Swarajya]]'' magazine opined that Haasan had \"inappropriately used this harmonious sacred chant to demonize Hinduism.\"<ref name=\"Swarajya\">{{Cite web |url=http://swarajyamag.com/current-affairs/vishwaroopam-the-stark-reality-facing-the-hindus |title=Vishwaroopam: The Stark Reality Facing the Hindus |last=Venkat |first=Kalavai |date=5 February 2013 |website=Swarajya |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160805130528/http://swarajyamag.com/current-affairs/vishwaroopam-the-stark-reality-facing-the-hindus |archive-date=5 August 2016 |access-date=5 August 2016}}</ref>\n[[File:Palacio de Bellas Artes - Mural El Hombre in cruce de caminos Rivera 4.jpg|thumb|right|alt=Painting by Diego Rivera|Mexican painter [[Diego Rivera]]'s [[fresco]], ''[[Man at the Crossroads]]'' served as an inspiration for Nallasivam's painting to indicate the atrocities committed by Kandasamy Padayatchi.<ref name=\"NS\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/and-brahma-said/article1423679.ece |title=And, Brahma said... |last=Sivashankar |first=Nithya |date=28 August 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=27 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327120847/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/and-brahma-said/article1423679.ece |archive-date=27 March 2016}}</ref>]]\nThe film critic [[Baradwaj Rangan]], in his review of another Haasan film, ''[[Vishwaroopam]]'' (2013), found the ethnicity of the characters in the film to be a continuation of Haasan's inclusion of non-Tamil characters in his films. Rangan considered this to be Haasan's acknowledgement of the \"interconnectedness of the nation\" and \"the world beyond India\". He pointed out in his article that Haasan had experimented with the concept before by including the usage of [[Bengali language]] and meeting [[Bengalis]] in ''[[Mahanadi (film)|Mahanadi]]'' (1994), a [[Telugu language|Telugu-speaking]] love interest in ''[[Nammavar]]'' (1994), marrying a Bengali woman in ''[[Hey Ram]]'' (2000), conducting investigations with an [[Americans|American]] associate in ''[[Vettaiyaadu Vilaiyaadu (2006 film)|Vettaiyaadu Vilaiyaadu]]'' (2006), and marriage to a [[French people|Frenchwoman]] in ''[[Manmadan Ambu]]'' (2010). Rangan notes that in ''Anbe Sivam'', the inclusion of and interaction with the [[Odia people]] was another example of including non-Tamil characters in his films.<ref name=\"Rangan\">{{Cite web |url=https://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2003/03/02/anbe-sivam/ |title=Anbe Sivam |last=Rangan |first=Baradwaj |authorlink=Baradwaj Rangan |date=2 March 2003 |website=baradwajrangan.wordpress.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328061721/https://baradwajrangan.wordpress.com/2003/03/02/anbe-sivam/ |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/vishwaroopam-terror-messages/article4392667.ece |title=Vishwaroopam: Terror messages |last=Rangan |first=Baradwaj |date=8 February 2013 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331152158/http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/vishwaroopam-terror-messages/article4392667.ece |archive-date=31 March 2016}}</ref> Rangan also compared Haasan's fight sequence with the use of an umbrella to the way he used a book and stool in ''[[Thoongathey Thambi Thoongathey]]'' (1983).<ref name=\"Rangan\" />\n\nAccording to a critic from [[Sify]], the basic plot of ''Anbe Sivam'' bears resemblance to the 1987 [[Road movie|road film]], ''[[Planes, Trains and Automobiles]]'' directed by [[John Hughes (filmmaker)|John Hughes]], which starred [[Steve Martin]] and [[John Candy]] in the lead roles. The critic noted Haasan and Madhavan's character share similar traits to that of the roles played by Candy and Martin in that film, respectively.<ref name=\"Sify Review\" /> The portrait painted by Nallasivam on the walls of Padayatchi's house is inspired by the Mexican painter [[Diego Rivera]]'s [[fresco]], ''[[Man at the Crossroads]]''.<ref name=\"NS\" /> The painting shows Nallasivam posing as Padayatchi's deity Shiva, the number 910 indicating the salary Padayatchi pays to his factory's workers, and the [[hammer and sickle]] communism symbol.<ref name=\"Swarajya1\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:09:40 to 1:11:20}} Aravindan Neelakandan from ''Swarajya'' commented on the influence of [[Marxism]] in the painting, believing it to be \"an empty vehicle to convey his ideology and is bereft of any intrinsic value in itself.\"<ref name=\"Swarajya1\" /> Srinivasa Ramanujam, writing for ''The Times of India'' in 2008, noted that the religious undertone in the film was similar to that of [[Rajinikanth]]'s ''[[Baba (2002 film)|Baba]]'' (2002).<ref name=\"Srinivasa Ramanujam 2008\">{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/An-avatar-in-his-own-right/articleshow/3123525.cms |title=An avatar in his own right |last=Ramanujam |first=Srinivasa |date=13 June 2008 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160410082809/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/An-avatar-in-his-own-right/articleshow/3123525.cms |archive-date=10 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Music ==\n{{Infobox album\n| name         = Anbe Sivam\n| type         = Soundtrack\n| artist       = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| cover        = \n| alt          = \n| released     = 11 December 2002\n| recorded     = 2002\n| venue        = \n| studio       = \n| genre        = [[Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length       = 35:16\n| language     = [[Tamil language|Tamil]]\n| label        = Ayngaran Music<br/>An Ak Audio<br/>Hit Musics\n| producer     = [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]]\n| prev_title   = [[Karmegham]]\n| prev_year    = 2002\n| next_title   = [[Anbu (2003 film)|Anbu]]\n| next_year    = 2003\n}}\n\nThe soundtrack album and background score for ''Anbe Sivam'' were composed by [[Vidyasagar (composer)|Vidyasagar]], and the lyrics for the songs were written by [[Vairamuthu]] and [[P. Vijay]].<ref name=\"MR\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/the-unassailable-in-action/article2614700.ece |title=The unassailable in action! |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |date=10 November 2011 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331145155/http://www.thehindu.com/features/friday-review/music/the-unassailable-in-action/article2614700.ece |archive-date=31 March 2016}}</ref> After composing the tune for the title song, Vidyasagar explained the situation of the song to Haasan, who wanted the song to be performed in such a way that the protagonist is singing according to the situation he finds himself in. Vidyasagar suggested that Haasan should sing the song himself to achieve the desired result, which the latter accepted.<ref name=\"SKJRediff\" /><ref name=\"SKJHindu\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701240300.htm |title=A thoroughly enjoyable experience |last=K. Jha |first=Subhash |date=17 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326061156/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/fr/2003/01/17/stories/2003011701240300.htm |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref> The song \"Mouname Paarvayai\" was not included in the film.<ref name=\"MR\" /> The song \"Poovaasam\" is based on the ''Shuddh Sarang'' [[raga]].{{efn|According to singer [[Charulatha Mani]], the ''Shuddh Sarang'' raga closely resembles the [[Carnatic raga]], ''[[Hamsanadam]]''.<ref name=\"ARJCM\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/call-of-the-swan/article4368746.ece |title=Call of the swan |last=Mani |first=Charulatha |date=1 February 2013 |work=The Hindu |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326053448/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/call-of-the-swan/article4368746.ece |archive-date=26 March 2016 |author-link=Charulatha Mani}}</ref>}} The male portions for the reprise of \"Poovaasam\" were sung by [[Sriram Parthasarathy]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/There-Can-Only-be-One-Ilaiyaraaja/2014/09/20/article2439914.ece |title=There Can Only be One Ilaiyaraaja |last=Subhakeerthana |first=S. |date=20 September 2014 |work=The New Indian Express |access-date=26 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160326065007/http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/There-Can-Only-be-One-Ilaiyaraaja/2014/09/20/article2439914.ece |archive-date=26 March 2016}}</ref>{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:05:15 to 1:09:40}} while the original version was sung by [[Vijay Prakash]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/Vijay-Prakash-Turns-Mall-into-Concert-Hall/2015/11/03/article3110229.ece |title=Vijay Prakash Turns Mall into Concert Hall |date=3 November 2015 |work=The New Indian Express |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328070441/http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/Vijay-Prakash-Turns-Mall-into-Concert-Hall/2015/11/03/article3110229.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> [[Sadhana Sargam]] sang her portion of both versions of the song.{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 1:05:15 to 1:09:40}}<ref name=\"Saavn\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.saavn.com/s/album/tamil/Anbe-Sivam-2001/4VOtd-CCoP8_ |title=Anbe Sivam (2002)&nbsp;\u2013 Tracklist |website=[[Saavn]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105070518/http://www.saavn.com/s/album/tamil/Anbe-Sivam-2001/4VOtd-CCoP8_ |archive-date=5 January 2017 |access-date=5 January 2017}}</ref>\n\nMalathi Rangarajan of ''The Hindu'' wrote, \"Vidyasagar is scaling great heights as a composer. The theme song and the melodious {{sic|\"Pon Vaasam\"|nolink=y}} are pointers. Vairamuthu's lyrics deserve special mention here.\"<ref name=\"MRReview\" /> Singer [[Charulatha Mani]], in her column for ''The Hindu'', \"A Raga's Journey\", noted, \"Poovaasam\" possessed \"a charm that is born out of classicism incorporated in a populist piece\".<ref name=\"ARJCM\" /> Arkay of [[Rediff.com]] found the songs to be \"at best, okay\".<ref name=\"Rediff Review\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/16anbe.htm |title=Why would Haasan make himself so ugly? |last=Arkay |date=16 January 2003 |website=Rediff.com |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328120741/http://www.rediff.com/movies/2003/jan/16anbe.htm |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> M. Suganth of ''The Times of India'', in his review for the music album, \"Lovers Special&nbsp;\u2013 Vol. 2\u20134\", included \"Poovaasam\" among the \"Hot Picks\" of the album.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2009/04/17/27/Ar02700.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=34477&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Lovers Special&nbsp;\u2013 Vol. 2\u20134 |last=Suganth |first=M. |date=17 April 2009 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105065709/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2009/04/17/27/Ar02700.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=34477&Keyword=(%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam)&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=5 January 2017}}</ref>\n{{clear}}\n{{Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| total_length = 35:16\n| headline = Track-List\n| title1 = Anbe Sivam\n| extra1 = [[Kamal Haasan]], [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]]\n| lyrics1 = \n| length1 = 04:22\n| title2 = Elo Machi\n| extra2 = Kamal Haasan, [[Udit Narayan]]\n| lyrics2 = \n| length2 = 04:37\n| title3 = Mouname Paarvayai\n| extra3 = [[S. P. Balasubrahmanyam]], Chandrayee\n| lyrics3 = \n| length3 = 04:39\n| title5 = Naatukkoru Seithi\n| extra5 = Kamal Haasan, Chandran\n| lyrics5 = \n| length5 = 08:12\n| title4 = Poovaasam\n| extra4 = [[Vijay Prakash]], [[Sadhana Sargam]]\n| lyrics4 = \n| length4 = 04:30\n| title6 = Elo Machi\n| note6 = Reprise\n| extra6 = Udit Narayan, [[Tippu (singer)|Tippu]]\n| lyrics6 = \n| length6 = 04:37\n| title7 = Poovaasam\n| note7 = Reprise\n| extra7 = [[Sriram Parthasarathy]], Sadhana Sargam\n| lyrics7 = \n| length7 = 04:25\n| all_writing = \n| title8 = \n| length8 = \n| title9 = \n| length9 = \n| title10 = \n| length10 = \n| all_lyrics = [[Vairamuthu]], except the song \"Mouname Paarvayai\" was written by [[Pa. Vijay]]\n}}\n\n== Release ==\nAccording to S. R. Ashok Kumar of ''The Hindu'', the producers were confident that ''Anbe Sivam'' would be a strong competitor at the [[50th National Film Awards]] that they had the film reviewed by the [[Central Board of Film Certification]] before the end of 2002 so that they could enter the film into the annual awards list.<ref name=\"SRAK\" />{{Sfn|Pyramid Movies|2014|loc=Clip from 00:00 to 00:03}} The film was released on 15 January 2003, which coincided with the [[Thai Pongal]] festival. It opened alongside five other films, including [[Vikram (actor)|Vikram]]'s ''[[Dhool]]'', [[Vijayakanth]]'s ''[[Chokka Thangam]]'', and ''[[Vaseegara (film)|Vaseegara]]'', which featured [[Vijay (actor)|Vijay]].<ref name=\"ASBBFC\" /><ref name=\"SRAK\" />\n\n''Anbe Sivam'' was screened as a part of the Indian Panorama section of the [[International Film Festival of India]] in 2003.<ref name=\"Panorama\" /> As a tribute to Safdar Hashmi, a special preview of the film was organised by Haasan in association with Safdar Hashmi Memorial Trust (SAHMAT) on 9 January 2003 at [[Siri Fort Auditorium]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://archives.peoplesdemocracy.in/2003/0119/01192003_anbesivam.htm |title=Kamal Haasan Pays Tribute to Safdar Hashmi Anbe Sivam Film Preview Show Held By SAHMAT |date=19 January 2003 |work=[[People's Democracy (newspaper)|People's Democracy]] |access-date=17 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517025109/http://archives.peoplesdemocracy.in/2003/0119/01192003_anbesivam.htm |archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref> The film was dubbed into Telugu as ''Sathyame Sivam'' and released on 28 February 2003.<ref name=\"Jeevi\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-sathyamesivam.html |title=Sathyame Sivam |last=Jeevi |date=28 February 2003 |website=[[Idlebrain.com]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328120937/http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/mr-sathyamesivam.html |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> It was dubbed into Hindi as ''Shivam'' two years later in 2005. After the release of the original Tamil version, the dubbing rights for the Hindi version were sold at a low price, much to the irritation of the lead actors as they were not able to dub for themselves in Hindi.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-in-hindi-news-tamil-kkfv6gjbbhf.html |title='Anbe Sivam' in Hindi |date=7 April 2005 |website=Sify |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328122006/http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-in-hindi-news-tamil-kkfv6gjbbhf.html |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Reception ==\n\n=== Critical response ===\nBaradwaj Rangan described the film as \"Kamal's latest solo attempt to bend, twist, shape-shift Tamil cinema into forms never-before seen.\"<ref name=\"Rangan\" /> In his review of the film's DVD, M. Suganth, writing for ''The Times of India'', called it \"one of the finest movies of the decade\" and praised the story, screenplay and dialogues before terming the film as \"a modern classic\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2008/05/02/52/Ar05200.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2008&DOCID=9635&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=Anbe Sivam (Drama/Comedy) |last=Suganth |first=M. |date=2 May 2008 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105065738/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2008/05/02/52/Ar05200.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2008&DOCID=9635&Keyword=(%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam)&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=5 January 2017}}</ref> Reviewing the Telugu dubbed version, ''Sathyame Sivam'', Jeevi of [[Idlebrain.com]] said that \"this art-kind-of film does entertain the people who love Kamal Hassan flicks\" while concluding that it \"would remain as one of the good films made in the recent times\".<ref name=\"Jeevi\" />\n\nMalathi Rangarajan of ''The Hindu'' believed that \"well-defined characters, a strong storyline and intelligent screenplay\" were the film's \"vital ingredients\". She further complimented Haasan's treatment of the story, and that his \"diligence that has gone into the chiselling of the story and screenplay is only too evident\", while calling the film \"a laudable effort\".<ref name=\"MRReview\" /> P.{{nbsp}}Devarajan of ''[[Business Line]]'' appreciated Haasan's performance and facial expressions and concluded his review by stating, \"This man has intrigued me and will always.\"<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2004/07/14/stories/2004071400272000.htm |title=The world of movies |last=Devarajan |first=P. |date=14 July 2004 |website=[[Business Line]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328061025/http://www.thehindubusinessline.com/2004/07/14/stories/2004071400272000.htm |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Another critic from ''The Hindu'', Gudipoodi Srihari, appreciated the pair of Haasan and Madhavan, noting that the duo \"make a fine combination of pals each with different mental make up, but goodness overflowing.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/03/04/stories/2003030400270400.htm |title=Worth watching |last=Srihari |first=Gudipoodi |date=4 March 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=12 June 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160612091518/http://www.thehindu.com/thehindu/mp/2003/03/04/stories/2003030400270400.htm |archive-date=12 June 2016}}</ref> Sujatha Narayanan, in a retrospective review for ''[[The New Indian Express]]'' commended Haasan's writing and Madhan's dialogue, finding them to be \"peppered with sharp wit, trivia and emotional depth.\"<ref name=\"SNNIE\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/jan/08/films-for-life-1747249.html |title=Films for life |last=Narayanan |first=Sujatha |date=8 January 2018 |work=The New Indian Express |access-date=9 January 2018 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180109174010/http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/2018/jan/08/films-for-life-1747249.html |archive-date=9 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nA reviewer from [[Sify]], in comparison, labelled the film as \"average\", stating that it was \"another predictable and corny film which is neither a comedy caper nor a class act.\"<ref name=\"Sify Review\" /> Similarly, Arkay of Rediff.com praised the performances of the lead cast but wrote the film \"tries to do too many things, and ends up failing at most, if not all, of them.\"<ref name=\"Rediff Review\" /> S.{{nbsp}}Anand of ''Outlook'' felt the film's thematic ideas of communism were presented in a \"cliched\" manner, and summarised by saying, \"If Rajnikant staked claim to divinity on a right-wing plank with ''Baba'', Kamal does it with pretensions to rationalist-left rhetoric.\"<ref name=\"Outlook\" />\n\n=== Box office ===\nDuring the first week of its theatrical run, an analysis by [[Sudhish Kamath]] of ''The Hindu'' showed the film to have grossed {{INR}}13.1&nbsp;million in Chennai alone.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/lf/2003/01/22/stories/2003012200790200.htm |title=New maths for the box office |last=Kamath |first=Sudhish |date=22 January 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160331154622/http://www.thehindu.com/lf/2003/01/22/stories/2003012200790200.htm |archive-date=31 March 2016 |author-link=Sudhish Kamath}}</ref>{{efn|name=exchange2003}} Despite this, the film [[Box office bomb|underperformed]] at the box office and incurred heavy losses for Lakshmi Movie Makers, effectively stopping them from investing in other ventures for the year 2003.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2003-08-26/news/27560133_1_tamil-film-ratnam-kavithalaya |title=Tamil films enter hit zone in 2003 |last=Govardan |first=D. |date=26 August 2003 |website=[[The Economic Times]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140308224817/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2003-08-26/news/27560133_1_tamil-film-ratnam-kavithalaya |archive-date=8 March 2014 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> An estimate by D.{{nbsp}}Govardan of ''[[The Economic Times]]'' places the losses at {{INR}}65&nbsp;million,<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2003-04-22/news/27562298_1_kamal-hassan-rajkamal-films-international-sandiyar |title=Funds elude Kamal Hassan's mega flick |last=Govardan |first=D. |date=22 April 2003 |website=The Economic Times |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20140308224811/http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2003-04-22/news/27562298_1_kamal-hassan-rajkamal-films-international-sandiyar |archive-date=8 March 2014 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>{{efn|name=exchange2003}} while Arun Ram of ''[[India Today]]'' states the losses incurred to be {{INR}}50&nbsp;million.<ref name=\"bg\" /><ref name=\"fs\">{{Cite news |url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kollywood-producer-venkateswaran-suicide-raises-fears-of-box-office-losses-empty-theatres/1/206486.html |title=Flop show |last=Ram |first=Arun |date=19 May 2003 |work=India Today |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328124535/http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kollywood-producer-venkateswaran-suicide-raises-fears-of-box-office-losses-empty-theatres/1/206486.html |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>{{efn|name=exchange2003}} Srinivasa Ramanujam of ''The Times of India'' compared the film's failure at the box office to that of ''Baba''.<ref name=\"Srinivasa Ramanujam 2008\" /> Both K. Muralitharan and Haasan defended the film's failure by blaming [[copyright infringement|video piracy]], with the latter stating that \"lots of people saw it, but they didn't pay\".<ref name=\"fs\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOIBG/2005/03/13/29/Ar02900.xml&CollName=TOI_BANGALORE_ARCHIVE&DOCID=285679&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=The Colour of My Cinema |last=Bala |first=Priya |date=13 March 2005 |website=The Times of India |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160411072313/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOIBG%2F2005%2F03%2F13%2F29%2FAr02900.xml&CollName=TOI_BANGALORE_ARCHIVE&DOCID=285679&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=11 April 2016 |access-date=11 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"|Award\n! scope=\"col\"|Date of ceremony\n! scope=\"col\"|Category\n! scope=\"col\"|Recipient(s) and nominee(s)\n! scope=\"col\"|Result\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"sortable\" | {{Abbr|Ref(s)|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"4\" | [[Filmfare Awards South]]\n| rowspan=\"4\" | [[51st Filmfare Awards South|12 June 2004]]\n| [[Filmfare Special Award&nbsp;\u2013 South|Special Jury Award]]\n| {{sort|Muralitharan|K. Muralitharan}}, V. Swaminathan, G. Venugopal\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"4\" |<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/51st-Annual-Manikchand-Filmfare-Award-winners/articleshow/718496.cms |title=51st Annual Manikchand Filmfare Award winners |date=4 June 2004 |work=The Times of India |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20150126140422/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/51st-Annual-Manikchand-Filmfare-Award-winners/articleshow/718496.cms |archive-date=26 January 2015}}</ref><br /><ref>{{Cite episode |title=51st Filmfare Awards South |series=Filmfare Awards |network=[[The Times Group]] |date=12 June 2004}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Film&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Film]]\n| {{sort|Muralitharan|K. Muralitharan}}, V. Swaminathan, G. Venugopal\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Actor]]\n| {{sort|Haasan|[[Kamal Haasan]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor&nbsp;\u2013 Tamil|Best Supporting Actor]]\n| {{sort|Madhavan|[[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]}}\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\" | South Indian Cinematographers Association (SICA) Awards\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 23 November 2003\n| Best Actor\n| {{sort|Haasan|Kamal Haasan}}\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\" |<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/lf/2003/11/26/stories/2003112602720200.htm |title=Glamour, song, dance and stars |last=Lakshmi |first=K. |date=26 November 2003 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328132448/http://www.thehindu.com/lf/2003/11/26/stories/2003112602720200.htm |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| Best Supporting Actor\n| {{sort|Madhavan|[[R. Madhavan|Madhavan]]}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Art Director\n| {{sort|Prabhaharan|M. Prabhaharan}}\n| {{won}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\" | [[Tamil Nadu State Film Awards]]\n|rowspan=\"2\" | 30 September 2004\n| [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]\n| {{sort|Madhavan|R.{{nbsp}}Madhavan}}<br /><small>(also for ''[[Kannathil Muthamittal]]'' and ''[[Run (2002 film)|Run]]'')</small>\n| {{won}}\n| style=\"text-align:center; \"rowspan=\"2\" |<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/2004/10/01/stories/2004100112290500.htm |title=6 film artistes win top award |date=1 October 2004 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160517093126/http://www.thehindu.com/2004/10/01/stories/2004100112290500.htm |archive-date=17 May 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Tamil Nadu State Film Award for Best Make-up Artist|Best Make-up Artist]]\n| {{sort|Rajan|V. P. Rajan}}\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n== Legacy ==\n{{Quote box\n |title =\n |quote = There's only one artiste in the whole Universe (!). It's Kamal Hassan. Without him there's no cinema. Have you watched ''Anbe Sivam''?\n |source =&nbsp;\u2013 Actor [[Nagesh]] in an interview with Malathi Rangarajan of ''The Hindu'' on whom he considered to be \"the best actor\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/behind-that-humorous-veneer/article2273149.ece |title=Behind that humorous veneer |last=Rangarajan |first=Malathi |date=27 July 2007 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328065205/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/behind-that-humorous-veneer/article2273149.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n |width  = 35%\n |align  = right\n}}\n\nFollowing its release, ''Anbe Sivam'' has attained [[cult film|cult status]] in Tamil cinema and receives re-runs on television channels.<ref name=\"SNNIE\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.news18.com/news/movies/happy-birthday-madhavan-6-roles-that-prove-he-has-an-amazing-acting-range-999699.html |title=Happy Birthday Madhavan: 6 roles that prove he has an amazing acting range |last=Rajpal |first=Roktim |date=1 July 2015 |website=[[CNN-News18]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105071022/http://www.news18.com/news/movies/happy-birthday-madhavan-6-roles-that-prove-he-has-an-amazing-acting-range-999699.html |archive-date=5 January 2017 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://indianexpress.com/photos/entertainment-gallery/happy-60th-birthday-kamal-haasan-top-roles/ |title=Happy 61st Birthday Kamal Haasan: The actor\u2019s top roles |date=7 November 2015 |work=The Indian Express |access-date=19 May 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105071355/http://indianexpress.com/photos/entertainment-gallery/happy-60th-birthday-kamal-haasan-top-roles/ |archive-date=5 January 2017 |page=13}}</ref> When the film was in post-production, Haasan revealed to film critic and journalist [[Subhash K. Jha]] that he was impressed with Madhavan's enthusiasm and performance during the making of the film, subsequently signing him to appear as the protagonist in his production venture, ''[[Nala Damayanthi (2003 film)|Nala Damayanthi]]'' (2003).<ref name=\"SKJRediff\" />\n\nBaradwaj Rangan wrote that ''Anbe Sivam'' was \"leagues ahead of the average Tamil{{snds}}why, even Indian{{snds}}film\", though he felt that \"the masses were unwilling to accept the experimental nature of the film\", while talking about the film's box office failure.<ref name=\"Rangan\" /> During his acceptance speech after winning the [[Vijay Award for Best Director]] in 2010 for ''[[Naan Kadavul]]'' (2009), director [[Bala (director)|Bala]] revealed that a scene in ''Anbe Sivam'' where Haasan says to Madhavan, \"when we love others unconditionally without any expectation, we become Gods\", inspired him to make his film.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-inspired-me-bala-news-tamil-kkfq35ahjhg.html |title=''Anbe Sivam'' inspired me: Bala |last=Dhananjayan |first=G. |date=1 June 2010 |website=Sify |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328061453/http://www.sify.com/movies/anbe-sivam-inspired-me-bala-news-tamil-kkfq35ahjhg.html |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Bala also made a reference to ''Anbe Sivam'' in his 2003 film, ''[[Pithamagan]]'', in a scene where [[Suriya]]'s character goes for a screening of the film with his friends.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2009/04/07/23/Ar02302.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=31318&Keyword=%28%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam%29&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |title=The Times of India&nbsp;\u2013 Did You Know? |date=7 April 2009 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105065754/http://epaper.timesofindia.com/Default/Scripting/ArticleWin.asp?From=Search&Key=TOICH/2009/04/07/23/Ar02302.xml&CollName=TOI_CHENNAI_ARCHIVE_2009&DOCID=31318&Keyword=(%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3EAnbe%3Cand%3E%3Cmany%3E%3Cstem%3ESivam)&skin=pastissues2&AppName=2&ViewMode=GIF |archive-date=5 January 2017}}</ref> A dialogue told by Haasan to Madhavan, \"Do you know what a [[tsunami]] is? ''Periya alai illa{{nbsp}}... malai''.\" (It's not just a big wave{{nbsp}}... it's a mountain) also attained popularity.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/What-did-Kamal-Haasan-teach-us/article16439215.ece |title=What did Kamal Haasan teach us? |last=Ramanujam |first=Srinivasa |date=7 November 2016 |work=The Hindu |access-date=31 October 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180105014954/http://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/What-did-Kamal-Haasan-teach-us/article16439215.ece |archive-date=5 January 2018 |last2=Menon |first2=Vishal}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, S.{{nbsp}}R. Ashok Kumar of ''The Hindu'' listed ''Anbe Sivam'' among the \"top five directorial ventures of Sundar{{nbsp}}C.\"<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/heading-for-a-hat-trick/article1433672.ece |title=Heading for a hat trick? |last=Kumar |first=S. R. Ashok |date=28 March 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328065541/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/heading-for-a-hat-trick/article1433672.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> In a 2008 interview with ''The Times of India'', Sundar{{nbsp}}C. stated that ''Anbe Sivam'' \"changed [him] personally and professionally\", making him a more confident person and altering his outlook towards life.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/A-producers-delight/articleshow/3467611.cms |title=A producer's delight! |date=11 September 2008 |work=The Times of India |access-date=10 April 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105070908/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/A-producers-delight/articleshow/3467611.cms |archive-date=5 January 2017}}</ref> He later contradicted his statement after revealing that the film's failure led him to become almost bankrupt and he remained unpaid for his work. The [[Income Tax Department]] froze his bank accounts for a year as he was not able to pay his taxes. He admitted that while he received praises for the film after its theatrical run, he would not make a film similar to ''Anbe Sivam'' anymore and that he chose to continue making commercial cinema, which he felt better matched his interests.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cinema.dinamalar.com/tamil-news/18919/cinema/Kollywood/I-lost-my-property-due-to-Anbe-Sivam-says-Sundar.C.htm |title=\u0b85\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc7 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bca\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0bb4\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc7\u0ba9\u0bcd \u2013 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bc8\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0bbf! |date=22 May 2014 |website=[[Dinamalar]] |language=Tamil |trans-title=I lost my property due to Anbe Sivam&nbsp;\u2013 An upset Sundar C! |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160714130237/http://cinema.dinamalar.com/tamil-news/18919/cinema/Kollywood/I-lost-my-property-due-to-Anbe-Sivam-says-Sundar.C.htm |archive-date=14 July 2016 |access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cinema.nakkheeran.in/Talkies.aspx?T=2085 |title=\"\u0b85\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc7 \u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0baa\u0b9f\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bc8 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bbf \u0b87\u0baf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bae\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc7\u0ba9\u0bcd\"&nbsp;\u2013 \u0b9a\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bb0\u0bcd.\u0b9a\u0bbf! |date=13 March 2013 |website=[[Nakkheeran]] |language=Tamil |trans-title=\"I will not direct films like Anbe Sivam anymore\"&nbsp;\u2013 Sundar C! |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130316033755/http://cinema.nakkheeran.in/Talkies.aspx?T=2085 |archive-date=16 March 2013 |access-date=13 April 2016}}</ref> In 2013, Haricharan Pudipeddi of the [[Indo-Asian News Service]] agency, included ''Anbe Sivam'' in his list of \"Kamal's most underrated films\". He believed the reason for the film's commercial failure was that audiences misunderstood the \"sarcastic undertones associated with atheism\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.sify.com/movies/on-his-59th-b-day-kamal-haasan-s-most-underrated-films-news-national-nlhk4gceibgsi.html |title=On his 59th b'day, Kamal Haasan's most underrated films |last=Pudipeddi |first=Haricharan |date=7 November 2013 |access-date=27 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160327132456/http://www.sify.com/movies/on-his-59th-b-day-kamal-haasan-s-most-underrated-films-news-national-nlhk4gceibgsi.html |archive-date=27 March 2016 |agency=[[Indo-Asian News Service]] |website=Sify}}</ref> On Haasan's birthday, 7 November 2015, Latha Srinivasan of ''[[Daily News and Analysis]]'' considered ''Anbe Sivam'' to be one of the \"films you must watch to grasp the breadth of Kamal Haasan's repertoire\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-birthday-special-films-you-must-watch-to-grasp-the-breadth-of-kamal-haasan-s-repertoire-2143008 |title=Birthday special: Films you must watch to grasp the breadth of Kamal Haasan's repertoire |last=Srinivasan |first=Latha |date=7 November 2015 |work=[[Daily News and Analysis]] |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6gL5edduL?url=http://www.dnaindia.com/entertainment/report-birthday-special-films-you-must-watch-to-grasp-the-breadth-of-kamal-haasan-s-repertoire-2143008 |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> The character of Nallasivam was ranked fourth in ''The Times of India'''s list of \"Kamal Haasan's top 10 mind-blowing avatars\".<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/Kamal-Haasans-top-10-mind-blowing-avatars/photostory/45058497.cms |title=Kamal Haasan's top 10 mind-blowing avatars |website=The Times of India |url-status=live |archive-url=https://archive.is/20170105071003/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/Kamal-Haasans-top-10-mind-blowing-avatars/photostory/45058497.cms |archive-date=5 January 2017 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn ''[[Vasool Raja MBBS]]'' (2004), the character Vasool Raja (Haasan), while attending a class asks whether being a doctor is equivalent to being God, and in doing so says \"Anbe Venkatachalam\", to which one of his classmates gently asks him, \"isn't it Anbe Sivam?\". Haasan retorts: \"Let it be. Let's try something different for a change.\"<ref>{{Cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QjTlT4VEiLc |title=Vasool Raja MBBS Tamil Movie&nbsp;\u2013 Kamal, Sneha, Prabhu, Prakash Raj |last=Kamal Haasan, Sneha, Prabhu Ganesan, Prakash Raj |year=2004 |place=India |access-date=8 January 2018 |website=[[YouTube]] |medium=motion picture}}</ref> The street theatre sequence featuring Kamal's character, Nallasivam, and his friends performing to make people aware of the atrocities committed by Nassar's character, Kanadasamy Padayatchi, was re-created at [[Tiruchirappalli]] in 2008 by Pralayan and his troupe from \"Chennai Kalai Kuzhu\" under the title ''Nammal Mudiyum''. In contrast, Pralayan's play explored gender inequality and domestic violence instead of unemployment.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/a-street-play-in-a-theatre-ambience/article1234535.ece |title=A street play in a theatre ambience |last=Aishwarya |first=S. |date=7 April 2008 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328074452/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/a-street-play-in-a-theatre-ambience/article1234535.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Kannada actor [[Vishnuvardhan (actor)|Vishnuvardhan]] noted in 2010 that fellow actor [[Sudeep]]'s film ''[[Just Maath Maathalli]]'' (2010) bears resemblance to ''Anbe Sivam''.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/its-more-than-mere-banter/article789113.ece |title=It's more than mere banter |last=Kumar |first=S. Shiva |date=12 February 2010 |website=The Hindu |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328072117/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/its-more-than-mere-banter/article789113.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016 |access-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> Hari Narayan, writing for ''The Hindu'' in 2014, mentions in his article on the Indian [[Rationalism|rationalist]] and author [[Narendra Dabholkar]] that [[Umesh Shukla]]'s ''[[OMG&nbsp;\u2013 Oh My God!]]'' (2012) was \"a toned down version of ''Anbe Sivam'' where rationality propels humans to find God in themselves, with flaws, which extols the virtue of becoming as much as that of being\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/blogs/blog-by-the-way/article5635194.ece |title=Fulcrum for the faithless souls |last=Narayan |first=Hari |date=31 January 2014 |work=The Hindu |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328073613/http://www.thehindu.com/opinion/blogs/blog-by-the-way/article5635194.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016}}</ref> In 2015 Uthiran of ''[[The Hindu (Tamil)|The Hindu]]'' in [[Tamil language|Tamil]], mentions in his review of ''[[Orange Mittai]]'' (2015) that the film's plot \"might remind viewers of ''Anbe Sivam''\".<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://tamil.thehindu.com/cinema/tamil-cinema/%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%A4%E0%AE%B2%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%AA%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%B0%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%B5%E0%AF%88-%E0%AE%86%E0%AE%B0%E0%AE%9E%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9A%E0%AF%81-%E0%AE%AE%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%9F%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9F%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%AF%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%87%E0%AE%A9%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%B3%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%8D/article7486062.ece |title=\u0bae\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc8: \u0b86\u0bb0\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0baf\u0bcd&nbsp;\u2013 \u0b87\u0ba9\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd |last=\u0b89\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba9\u0bcd |date=31 July 2015 |work=[[The Hindu (Tamil)|The Hindu]] |access-date=28 March 2016 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160328093400/http://tamil.thehindu.com/cinema/tamil-cinema/%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%A4%E0%AE%B2%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%AA%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%B0%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%B5%E0%AF%88-%E0%AE%86%E0%AE%B0%E0%AE%9E%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9A%E0%AF%81-%E0%AE%AE%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%9F%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%9F%E0%AE%BE%E0%AE%AF%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%87%E0%AE%A9%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%8D-%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%B3%E0%AE%BF%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%8D%E0%AE%AA%E0%AF%81%E0%AE%AE%E0%AF%8D/article7486062.ece |archive-date=28 March 2016 |language=Tamil |trans-title=First Look: Orange Mittai&nbsp;\u2014 The pros and cons}}</ref> In 2017, Ashok, who directed the comedy film ''[[Peechankai]]'', mentions he was inspired by ''Anbe Sivam'' to become a director.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/director-of-peechaankai-ashok-talks-about-his-film/article19055414.ece |title=Director Ashok talks about his first feature, the quirky 'Peechaankai' |last=J. Rao |first=Subha |date=15 June 2017 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 June 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617083107/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/director-of-peechaankai-ashok-talks-about-his-film/article19055414.ece |archive-date=17 June 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/peechankai-review-the-left-comes-to-power/article19087971.ece |title='Peechankai': the left comes to power |last=Ramanujam |first=Srinivasa |date=16 June 2017 |work=The Hindu |access-date=17 June 2017 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170617083112/http://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/reviews/peechankai-review-the-left-comes-to-power/article19087971.ece |archive-date=17 June 2017}}</ref>\n\n== Notes ==\n{{Notelist}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== Film ==\n* {{cite AV media | url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qFA7REldr88 | title=Anbe Sivam Tamil Full Movie&nbsp;\u2013 Kamal Haasan, Madhavan, Kiran | publisher=[[Pyramid Saimira|Pyramid Movies]] | date=30 May 2014 | accessdate=26 March 2016 | 